04:09.583 --> 04:10.834
this cannot be.

04:11.042 --> 04:15.004
The worlds of magic and logic
must exist side by side,

04:15.297 --> 04:16.964
not destroy each other.

04:20.927 --> 04:24.972
Take care! Be careful
with your machines, I say!

04:26.266 --> 04:27.976
Who's makin'
all that rumpus?!

04:28.185 --> 04:31.354
It's that old gent
that lives upstream!

04:31.563 --> 04:34.649
Your motors must not
crowd out all magic

04:35.108 --> 04:36.651
or the world is lost!

04:37.027 --> 04:39.487
Some sort of magician,
i hear.

04:40.197 --> 04:43.617
I am carolinus,
the green wizard!

04:43.825 --> 04:45.451
You're loony, you are!

04:45.660 --> 04:46.994
Get back
to where you belong!

04:47.204 --> 04:49.289
I belong everywhere,

04:49.664 --> 04:52.416
for my domain
is the green world --

04:52.793 --> 04:55.921
nature itself
and all its inhabitants!

05:10.227 --> 05:12.437
Away with your mill wheel --

05:12.938 --> 05:16.441
a ball of blue magic
to make it disappear!

05:16.650 --> 05:18.818
[Vibrating 1

05:22.322 --> 05:24.490
disappear, say I!

05:25.033 --> 05:26.200
Aah!

05:32.999 --> 05:34.917
"Magic," he calls it.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.462
My little boy
could do better!

05:51.893 --> 05:53.811
Father, you need rest.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.271
No time.

05:56.398 --> 05:58.691
It just was not there.

05:59.442 --> 06:02.236
I called upon magic,
and there was none.

06:02.696 --> 06:04.155
Oh.

06:04.823 --> 06:06.074
The pain again?

06:06.283 --> 06:10.036
I can't let it bother me.
Have you written the messages?

06:10.245 --> 06:11.329
Yes, but --

06:11.538 --> 06:13.790
then summon the silver owls.

06:13.999 --> 06:16.376
- But --
- summon them, <i>I</i> say!

06:24.301 --> 06:26.886
Is it true?
Did they stone you?

06:27.137 --> 06:29.931
Ah, me and young gorbash
will fix 'em!

06:30.515 --> 06:31.641
We'll burn down that mill

06:31.850 --> 06:34.102
and devour
every livin' one of 'em!

06:34.311 --> 06:35.520
That would do no good.

06:36.021 --> 06:38.189
Just a little scare,
then, huh --

06:38.398 --> 06:41.651
a short fiery blast
to turn their hair white, huh?

06:41.860 --> 06:43.111
Smrgol, please!

06:43.320 --> 06:45.155
Father, the owls!

06:49.367 --> 06:52.578
Smrgol, I'm summoning
my brothers to a meeting --

06:52.787 --> 06:54.955
our first in four centuries.

06:55.498 --> 06:56.665
Away !

06:57.000 --> 06:57.875
Ommadon too?

06:58.084 --> 07:01.253
The ancient laws
command he be included.

07:01.463 --> 07:03.298
Make gorbash ready
for the journey

07:03.506 --> 07:05.424
to the temple
of all antiquity.

07:05.634 --> 07:08.261
I wish I could carry you,
old friend.

07:08.470 --> 07:10.680
You've served me well
in the past.

07:10.889 --> 07:14.100
Let young gorbash
bear your burdens now.

07:17.062 --> 07:18.646
Father,
who are these brothers?

07:19.064 --> 07:20.732
You've never
spoken to me of them.

07:21.066 --> 07:23.401
I know you are green wizard
of nature's realm,

07:23.610 --> 07:24.360
but the others?

07:24.569 --> 07:27.113
My brother solarius
is the blue wizard,

07:27.656 --> 07:29.532
<i>lord of the depths
and heights.</i>

07:30.116 --> 07:31.909
<i>His realm is outer space,</i>

07:32.327 --> 07:35.163
<i>deepest ocean,
highest mountain.</i>

07:36.247 --> 07:39.416
My brother calls counsel,
but why?

07:39.834 --> 07:40.918
Lunarian!

07:41.169 --> 07:42.170
Lunarian!

07:49.552 --> 07:53.430
<i>Carolinus: And my brother
lotagal, the golden wizard</i> --

07:53.890 --> 07:55.433
<i>his realm is light and air.</i>

07:55.642 --> 07:59.896
<i>He is lord of transcendence,
healing, contemplation.</i>

08:01.856 --> 08:03.274
I was expecting this.

08:03.525 --> 08:04.859
It was inevitable.

08:05.694 --> 08:07.237
Shin tsu -- shin tsu!

08:12.575 --> 08:15.369
<i>Carofinus". And finally,
high in loathly tower,</i>

08:15.704 --> 08:20.204
<i>my last brother, ommadon,
the red wizard,</i>

08:22.043 --> 08:26.255
<i>lord of the devil's domain,
seducer of darkness,</i>

08:26.464 --> 08:29.467
<i>master of that heartless magic
the world calls black.</i>

08:34.014 --> 08:35.222
Briag!

08:35.682 --> 08:36.890
Briag!

08:37.892 --> 08:42.104
My fool brother has just
realized the inevitable.

08:42.981 --> 08:44.607
Well, I'll go.

08:45.817 --> 08:48.486
It should prove amusing.

08:50.280 --> 08:52.240
Briag, I say!

08:59.205 --> 09:02.291
<i>Carohnus: Astride the terrible
briag, he is absolute ruler</i>

09:02.500 --> 09:05.586
<i>of that inferno-like mass
of primordial filth</i>

09:05.795 --> 09:07.505
<i>which is his domain.</i>

09:09.382 --> 09:11.258
<i>Young woman".
Why does antiquity force you</i>

09:11.468 --> 09:13.678
<i>to include something
so abominable?</i>

09:13.887 --> 09:16.222
<i>As evil is a part
of all things,</i>

09:16.556 --> 09:19.058
<i>evil is a part
of our world of magic,</i>

09:19.684 --> 09:21.352
for the irony
of all existence

09:21.561 --> 09:23.771
is that good
would be totally impotent

09:24.189 --> 09:25.982
without the contrast of evil.

09:26.524 --> 09:28.776
Oh, father, take care.

09:29.778 --> 09:31.362
Gorbash stands ready.

09:31.571 --> 09:33.573
Then I am on my way.

09:38.620 --> 09:41.706
Whither dost thou
command me, oh, master?

09:41.998 --> 09:45.292
Gorbash, for pity's sake,
no formality, please.

09:46.086 --> 09:48.379
Well, I, uh, like to
do things by the book.

09:48.588 --> 09:50.715
To the temple
of all antiquity.

09:51.091 --> 09:52.759
Right. Where?

09:52.967 --> 09:55.636
I'll guide you as we go.
Away!

10:20.411 --> 10:21.203
Dear brothers...

10:21.412 --> 10:24.415
We meet today
in the temple of all antiquity.

10:24.624 --> 10:25.958
Come, come.

10:26.167 --> 10:29.170
Get on with it.
Why did you summon us?

10:29.379 --> 10:31.089
As you must have noticed,

10:31.297 --> 10:34.216
our magic powers
have been growing dim.

10:34.551 --> 10:36.094
I have so noticed.

10:36.302 --> 10:39.388
It is because man is choosing
logic over magic.

10:39.597 --> 10:40.556
But why?

10:40.765 --> 10:43.559
Because logic is so...
Logical.

10:43.768 --> 10:46.061
So what are you
going to do --

10:46.312 --> 10:50.812
sit around like a bunch of
old nannies and let it happen?

10:52.652 --> 10:54.570
Please, hear me out.

10:57.699 --> 11:02.199
I propose we create
the last realm of magic.

11:04.706 --> 11:06.624
Magnificent!

11:07.375 --> 11:09.043
Incredible!

11:12.630 --> 11:14.423
Carolinus:
The magic realm --

11:14.632 --> 11:17.009
where all enchanted things
might retreat

11:17.218 --> 11:18.761
before their age ends.

11:19.095 --> 11:21.430
If we consolidate
our powers,

11:21.639 --> 11:25.017
there will be enough magic
left to create such a place,

11:25.393 --> 11:27.478
sealed off from
the rest of the world

11:27.770 --> 11:30.063
by the mists
of invisibility.

11:30.481 --> 11:33.192
You would defeat
science and logic

11:33.401 --> 11:36.946
with a foolish
retirement village?

11:43.036 --> 11:45.705
Not defeat,
my brother, enhance.

11:46.122 --> 11:48.165
The world, though it
does not realize it,

11:48.374 --> 11:51.835
cannot do without magic.
For example --

11:52.045 --> 11:55.673
<i>man hears of the dragon's
invulnerable skin, and lo,</i>

11:55.965 --> 11:58.592
<i>he makes armor,
battleships, tanks.</i>

11:59.719 --> 12:03.222
<i>The fairy flies,
and furiously jealous,</i>

12:03.431 --> 12:05.808
<i>man himself defies gravity</i>

12:06.017 --> 12:08.769
<i>with machines
he will call airplanes.</i>

12:09.562 --> 12:12.147
<i>A magician looks
into his crystal</i>

12:12.357 --> 12:16.152
<i>and sees and hears
halfway across the world.</i>

12:16.361 --> 12:20.031
<i>"Ahh," says man,
"lf only it could be so,"</i>

12:20.448 --> 12:23.951
<i>and centuries from now,
he conjures up miracles</i>

12:24.244 --> 12:26.454
<i>but calls them
radio and television.</i>

12:27.580 --> 12:30.457
If man is to surmount
the insurmountable,

12:30.833 --> 12:34.002
there must always be magic
to inspire him.

12:34.587 --> 12:36.589
The world needs magic.

12:37.131 --> 12:38.757
Magic cannot die.

12:38.967 --> 12:40.718
[Applauds 1

12:40.927 --> 12:42.386
it shall be.

12:42.595 --> 12:45.014
I will bring you
distant stars,

12:45.223 --> 12:46.724
wonders from the sea.

12:47.058 --> 12:49.226
And I will bring you peace
and Harmony

12:49.477 --> 12:52.771
so that every magic thing
might live together and share

12:52.981 --> 12:54.399
what enchantment remains.

12:54.607 --> 12:56.400
No! Never!

12:57.151 --> 13:01.651
I will not concede defeat
by this modern world.

13:01.948 --> 13:06.327
I will not retire
to this fool's paradise!

13:06.536 --> 13:08.246
But we have no choice!

13:08.705 --> 13:11.624
Inevitability is
the strongest magic of all!

13:11.833 --> 13:15.545
<i>I</i> have weapons
you would not dare use.

13:15.920 --> 13:18.631
<i>Fear</i> rules man.

13:19.340 --> 13:23.260
By summoning
all the dark powers,

13:23.469 --> 13:27.264
I will infest
the spirit of man

13:27.765 --> 13:32.265
so that he uses his science
and logic to destroy himself.

13:35.940 --> 13:38.609
What havoc and rage --

13:39.652 --> 13:41.945
<i>turn brother against brother.</i>

13:43.031 --> 13:46.784
<i>Greed and avarice
shall prevail.</i>

13:47.493 --> 13:50.245
<i>And those who do not
hear my words</i>

13:50.455 --> 13:52.790
<i>shall pay the price.</i>

13:55.626 --> 14:00.126
I'll <i>teach man
to use his machines.</i>

14:00.673 --> 14:05.173
I'll <i>show him what distorted
science can give birth to.</i>

14:07.180 --> 14:10.933
<i>I'll</i> teach him
to fly like a fairy.

14:11.934 --> 14:14.603
<i>And</i> I'll <i>give
the ultimate answer</i>

14:14.812 --> 14:18.357
<i>to all his science can ask.</i>

14:19.609 --> 14:24.109
And the world will be free
for my magic again!

14:28.534 --> 14:31.078
Stop! This must not be!

14:31.287 --> 14:33.622
We want none
of your dark magic!

14:40.213 --> 14:44.713
While your powers die,
mine will flourish!

14:46.135 --> 14:49.555
Man will never
inherit my domain,

14:49.764 --> 14:53.601
for I am making man mine!

14:54.435 --> 14:58.772
He will understand
and come to desire my magic.

14:59.190 --> 15:02.443
It is inevitable.

15:02.735 --> 15:04.278
You shall see.

15:06.072 --> 15:10.572
This dark determination
i swear...

15:11.744 --> 15:14.371
By this red crown...

15:15.331 --> 15:19.626
...source
of all my dark power,

15:20.420 --> 15:22.713
so be it...

15:23.464 --> 15:26.675
Now and forever!

15:28.553 --> 15:29.762
Farewell!

15:30.596 --> 15:32.514
Can you not feel
the world

15:32.807 --> 15:36.435
turning in my direction
already?

15:42.608 --> 15:44.693
Can his dark magic
be stopped?

15:44.902 --> 15:46.528
Only by invading his realm

15:46.737 --> 15:50.073
and capturing that cursed
red crown from his head.

15:50.283 --> 15:51.951
You may include me.

15:52.160 --> 15:54.370
I will bring
the fire of the meteors,

15:54.579 --> 15:56.706
the rage of the seven seas!

16:04.881 --> 16:06.507
What was that all about?

16:06.716 --> 16:09.802
Antiquity will not allow us
to become involved.

16:10.261 --> 16:13.597
The eternal laws of enchantment
expressly forbid

16:13.806 --> 16:16.600
the four magic brothers
from warring on one another.

16:16.809 --> 16:18.769
Oh, quite right.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.229
Terribly sorry.

16:20.438 --> 16:21.814
But what can we do?

16:22.106 --> 16:23.982
We must inspire a quest

16:24.192 --> 16:28.196
with its sacred mission to steal
the red crown of ommadon.

16:28.404 --> 16:31.782
We will enlist the aid of allies
who share our beliefs --

16:31.991 --> 16:35.828
mortals, enchanted folk,
beasts, dragons.

16:36.037 --> 16:38.706
All such creatures
in my dominion are peaceful --

16:39.123 --> 16:40.374
hardly suitable.

16:40.583 --> 16:43.460
I can inspire
Neptune himself to join,

16:43.669 --> 16:46.838
and great whales
and serpents of the sea!

16:47.131 --> 16:50.342
Unfortunately, the quest
will be waged on land.

16:50.551 --> 16:51.510
It's no good, brothers.

16:51.719 --> 16:55.597
It seems I and I alone
can inspire such a mission.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.599
Whom will you send?

16:57.850 --> 17:02.187
Well, first, my old friend,
sir orren Neville-Smythe,

17:02.396 --> 17:03.605
a gallant knight and true.

17:03.814 --> 17:04.564
And?

17:04.773 --> 17:06.400
My dragon gorbash.

17:06.776 --> 17:10.320
He's young and impetuous,
but incredibly strong and brave.

17:10.530 --> 17:14.032
And? There must be three
to begin a magic quest.

17:14.407 --> 17:15.867
The laws so command.

17:16.160 --> 17:18.328
There will be another --
a leader.

17:18.538 --> 17:21.207
- Vvho?
- I haven't the slightest idea.

17:21.415 --> 17:22.457
How, then?

17:22.666 --> 17:25.377
Tonight, after you both
have returned to your realms,

17:25.586 --> 17:27.921
I will turn to antiquity
for the choice.

17:28.297 --> 17:30.382
Its wisdom shall prevail.

17:31.384 --> 17:33.844
Well, whoever
antiquity chooses,

17:34.053 --> 17:36.889
your leader will have
his job cut out for him.

17:37.265 --> 17:40.643
I leave him this --
the shield of saturn.

17:41.060 --> 17:43.854
Forged from the mystic dust
of her rings,

17:44.063 --> 17:47.024
it will deflect
<i>any</i> dark magic spell.

17:47.275 --> 17:51.028
I have only implements of peace,
but perhaps he will find

17:51.237 --> 17:53.197
the flute
of healing sleep useful.

17:53.489 --> 17:56.074
It is from
the temple of the muses.

17:56.284 --> 17:57.868
When played, it will lull

17:58.077 --> 18:00.537
the most fearsome dragon
to sleep.

18:00.746 --> 18:02.247
Thank you, good brothers.

18:02.456 --> 18:06.956
Ommadon will not prevail,
and his crown shall be captured.

18:08.421 --> 18:09.296
So be it!

18:09.505 --> 18:12.049
May victory be ours!

18:17.805 --> 18:19.515
Hey, a war at last!

18:19.724 --> 18:21.600
Finally, I will see battle!

18:21.809 --> 18:24.144
Not a war, a <i>quest.</i>

18:24.353 --> 18:27.147
Well, whatever you call it,
I'm ready for it!

18:27.356 --> 18:30.025
Unfortunately,
so is ommadon.

18:48.377 --> 18:50.670
Carolinus:
Hear me now, antiquity!

18:51.297 --> 18:55.797
Hear me, great conglomeration
of spirits gone before!

18:56.469 --> 18:58.137
Make your will known!

18:58.888 --> 19:02.808
Who shall lead the quest
to capture the crown of ommadon?

19:07.396 --> 19:09.564
<i>Search the future.</i>

19:10.149 --> 19:13.902
<i>He will be the distant
descendant of great Peter,</i>

19:14.195 --> 19:15.779
<i>the dragon master.</i>

19:16.322 --> 19:19.450
Oh, I have heard
legends of great Peter.

19:19.992 --> 19:21.868
Centuries ago,
he tamed the dragons

19:22.078 --> 19:23.454
and taught them to speak.

19:23.663 --> 19:28.163
<i>777 generations
separate great Peter</i>

19:28.918 --> 19:31.003
<i>from he whom you seek.</i>

19:31.212 --> 19:34.381
By why so many generations
away from the original?

19:34.590 --> 19:37.175
<i>He is the first
of the descendants</i>

19:37.510 --> 19:39.678
<i>who is a man of science.</i>

19:40.054 --> 19:41.597
Why should that
be important?

19:42.014 --> 19:45.100
<i>Trust the judgment
of antiquity!</i>

19:45.309 --> 19:47.686
I do! I do -- implicitly.

19:48.062 --> 19:52.562
Tell me, in which century
will I find this champion?

19:53.150 --> 19:57.650
<i>10 hence from this --
our 9,000th.</i>

19:58.114 --> 20:02.159
That would make it the 20th
century by man's calendar.

20:02.368 --> 20:04.661
<i>The closing decades.</i>

20:07.873 --> 20:09.332
A silver acorn?

20:09.750 --> 20:12.544
<i>Drop it into
the limpid pool of time,</i>

20:13.087 --> 20:14.755
<i>and you will find him.</i>

20:15.214 --> 20:18.258
<i>And now, farewell.</i>

20:26.600 --> 20:30.020
Are you certain this is
the limpid pool of time?

20:30.229 --> 20:32.481
My dear young fellow,
i am one of

20:32.690 --> 20:34.108
the four magic brothers.

20:34.316 --> 20:37.485
I should know a limpid pool
of time when I see one.

20:40.990 --> 20:45.285
Man: Dragons and wizards
and dungeons and princesses --

20:45.870 --> 20:47.329
dragons and wizards

20:47.538 --> 20:51.083
and princesses and dungeons
and castles --

20:52.042 --> 20:55.920
Mr. Dickinson,
is this all you think about?

20:56.130 --> 20:57.339
Never mind what <i>I</i> think.

20:57.548 --> 20:59.967
What do you think of this
new "flight of dragons" game?

21:00.176 --> 21:02.761
It's fun.
What can I say?

21:03.137 --> 21:04.721
Just a couple
of thousand dollars,

21:04.930 --> 21:06.014
we can manufacture this,

21:06.223 --> 21:07.974
and we'll all be
livin' like kings!

21:08.184 --> 21:10.811
"Just a couple of thousand,"
he says,

21:11.270 --> 21:12.729
like it was peanuts.

21:12.938 --> 21:15.273
This is an heirloom.
It must be worth something.

21:15.483 --> 21:18.194
Your "heirs"
didn't "loom" so big.

21:18.402 --> 21:21.071
If I give you $50,
I'd be fired.

21:21.280 --> 21:23.031
"Flight of dragons" --

21:23.240 --> 21:25.784
aren't you writing
a book by the same name?

21:26.118 --> 21:28.453
<i>Was.</i> I don't have time
to work on it now --

21:28.662 --> 21:30.330
not with holding down
two jobs,

21:30.539 --> 21:31.957
but if this game sells --

21:32.166 --> 21:34.334
you know something,
Mr. Dickinson?

21:34.543 --> 21:38.630
Nothing personal,
but you're a real dragon nut.

21:39.715 --> 21:42.008
They fascinate me --
always have.

21:42.218 --> 21:44.845
I'm sure they
really existed at one time.

21:45.095 --> 21:48.473
See, I'm trying to dope out
how they breathe fire --

21:48.682 --> 21:50.684
I take back the "nut" part.

21:51.018 --> 21:52.644
<i>You're a dragon fanatic.</i>

21:52.853 --> 21:55.772
Right. I eat,
breathe, and sleep 'em.

21:55.981 --> 21:58.149
I hope to become a member
of england's dragon society,

21:58.359 --> 21:59.985
and I live here in Boston.

22:00.194 --> 22:01.445
Your turn, evil wizard.

22:01.654 --> 22:05.616
Why am I always
the bad guy?! Nine!

22:05.825 --> 22:10.287
Ha-ha! I got you blocked
in the enchanted ice passage --

22:10.496 --> 22:12.456
frozen stiff!

22:12.665 --> 22:15.334
Yeah, but an 11 will give me
dragon fire to melt it.

22:15.543 --> 22:17.586
That's going to be
our leader?!

22:18.087 --> 22:21.507
That's the <i>777th</i> son of --

22:21.715 --> 22:23.758
antiquity must know.

22:23.968 --> 22:25.678
Trust antiquity.

22:25.886 --> 22:28.179
How's he gonna stand up
to ommadon

22:28.389 --> 22:30.057
playing with toy dragons?

22:30.266 --> 22:33.394
Look! Look closely
at those small chessmen

22:33.602 --> 22:34.936
<i>he's playing with!</i>

22:35.563 --> 22:38.941
<i>The piece the pawnbroker
is playing with is ommadon!</i>

22:39.859 --> 22:42.528
<i>And there's me
and my brothers!</i>

22:43.404 --> 22:45.239
<i>Dickinson's piece is you!</i>

22:46.115 --> 22:48.992
<i>And in the background,
Princess melisande!</i>

22:49.910 --> 22:52.162
<i>Extraordinary!</i>

22:53.163 --> 22:57.083
<i>Somehow, Dickinson
knows what we look like!</i>

22:57.293 --> 22:58.419
<i>Somehow --</i>

23:00.254 --> 23:02.047
good old antiquity!

23:02.381 --> 23:04.716
I knew I could trust it!

23:05.384 --> 23:08.970
Gorbash, fly to
silvenair and wait for me.

23:09.388 --> 23:12.557
Tell melisande to summon
sir orren Neville-Smythe.

23:12.766 --> 23:14.058
Where are you going?

23:21.817 --> 23:24.820
Bring me to him!
I insist!

23:28.866 --> 23:30.450
What the heck happened?

23:31.619 --> 23:34.496
Hey, are you deaf
or something?

23:34.705 --> 23:36.373
Carolinus:
A splendid game!

23:36.874 --> 23:38.417
Come down and join it!

23:39.126 --> 23:39.835
What?!

23:40.586 --> 23:44.089
<i>Untranto kala!</i>

23:45.591 --> 23:47.843
12! Ha ha ha!

23:48.052 --> 23:49.595
There's no beating that!

23:49.803 --> 23:52.222
Come down, I say!
<i>Kala!</i>

23:53.057 --> 23:54.308
[Vibrating 1

23:58.270 --> 23:59.062
what happened?

23:59.271 --> 24:01.273
I'll explain
during the journey.

24:01.523 --> 24:02.565
Journey?

24:02.775 --> 24:07.275
<i>Sit</i> down!
<i>Szvisumaad kala!</i>

24:20.084 --> 24:22.836
Keep your wits.
We're almost there.

24:23.045 --> 24:24.755
That's what you
said before!

24:24.964 --> 24:26.048
Since those dice
burned out,

24:26.256 --> 24:28.466
it seems like we've
been falling for hours!

24:28.676 --> 24:32.137
Actually, it's been
more like 10 centuries!

24:34.807 --> 24:37.935
Welcome home, carolinus!

24:38.143 --> 24:40.019
Good old smrgol!

24:40.813 --> 24:42.397
A dragon!

24:42.731 --> 24:46.484
I'm actually seeing
a dragon -- a real dragon!

24:46.694 --> 24:48.654
Call me smrgol!

24:48.862 --> 24:52.532
Son of a gun -- a dragon!
I'm talking to a dragon!

24:52.741 --> 24:54.367
I'll get you down!

25:08.424 --> 25:09.716
A dragon!

25:09.925 --> 25:12.010
I'm riding
a blooming dragon!

25:12.219 --> 25:14.054
What'd you call me?!

25:14.263 --> 25:16.640
Ow! Turn your head.

25:16.849 --> 25:19.017
Whoops! I'm sorry.

25:19.226 --> 25:21.728
I've just been singed
by dragon fire!

25:21.937 --> 25:23.688
What a great way to travel!

25:32.156 --> 25:35.868
Well, if you
don't need me any longer,

25:36.785 --> 25:39.746
I hear the call
of my comrades --

25:40.748 --> 25:43.250
a mating dance, perhaps.

25:43.751 --> 25:46.378
Really, smrgol, at your age!

25:53.010 --> 25:57.347
You wanted dragons, my son.
Dragons you shall have.

25:57.598 --> 25:58.932
I'll never understand.

25:59.141 --> 26:01.017
All those toy chessmen
i carved --

26:01.226 --> 26:03.144
those dragons
and wizards --

26:03.353 --> 26:05.438
how did I know
what you look like?

26:05.647 --> 26:08.900
Why question?
Just trust antiquity.

26:09.860 --> 26:11.736
Am I dreaming all this?

26:11.945 --> 26:14.530
Am I on the game board
or in reality?

26:14.740 --> 26:18.493
Perhaps
somewhere in between.

26:18.702 --> 26:21.955
Imagination is the most potent
of all magic.

26:22.664 --> 26:23.498
Look!

26:23.749 --> 26:26.209
Another of your creations
come to life...

26:26.460 --> 26:28.628
Father! Father!

26:28.837 --> 26:31.256
...the Princess melisande.

26:31.799 --> 26:34.218
My fairy Princess.

26:34.593 --> 26:38.513
Oh, I made her everything
I'd ever desired in a woman.

26:38.722 --> 26:40.807
Well,
what I mean to say...

26:41.016 --> 26:44.185
What you mean to say
is just what you said.

26:44.394 --> 26:46.646
- Will I meet her?
- Yes...

26:47.981 --> 26:49.524
But not dressed like that --

26:49.733 --> 26:53.903
department-store seersucker
all charred by dragon exhaust.

26:54.488 --> 26:58.950
<i>Convento serculum kala!</i>

27:01.245 --> 27:02.746
I hope the fit is correct.

27:03.038 --> 27:04.581
As I explained
during the drop,

27:04.790 --> 27:07.542
my magic is quite limited
these days.

27:09.962 --> 27:13.840
Your highness,
may I present, uh...

27:14.591 --> 27:15.800
Sir Peter.

27:16.009 --> 27:19.804
Sir Peter, this is
the Princess melisande.

27:20.597 --> 27:21.681
Your highness.

27:22.141 --> 27:24.351
Oh, you must be he

27:24.560 --> 27:27.145
who my guardian has sought
to save our world.

27:27.938 --> 27:31.399
Uh, I...Suppose I am.

27:32.067 --> 27:32.734
Am i'.>

27:32.943 --> 27:34.861
trust in antiquity.

27:35.279 --> 27:38.323
Did you summon sir orren
Neville-Smythe, as I requested?

27:38.532 --> 27:40.283
He'll be here
by dawn tomorrow.

27:40.742 --> 27:43.286
Gorbash:
Carolinus! Hello!

27:43.495 --> 27:45.246
Another one!

27:45.455 --> 27:47.457
Hey, look at what
I've been saving!

27:47.666 --> 27:50.335
It's gold, gold, gold!

27:50.544 --> 27:52.629
Oh, that pain again.

27:52.838 --> 27:55.799
I've asked him
not to bellow so.

27:56.091 --> 27:58.343
Simply magnificent sight!

27:58.552 --> 28:03.052
But, sir Peter, it is only
gorbash, our house dragon.

28:03.390 --> 28:04.557
House dragon?

28:04.766 --> 28:06.601
You've met
the entire family.

28:06.935 --> 28:09.437
Gorbash,
this is sir Peter.

28:09.646 --> 28:11.481
Oh, yes.
How do you do?

28:11.690 --> 28:16.190
See? A soup tureen --
a bowl to you -- of solid gold!

28:17.487 --> 28:20.740
Really, gorbash, if your hoard
grows much larger,

28:20.949 --> 28:22.951
there will be no room
for furniture in the house.

28:23.160 --> 28:25.328
Blast! That's what
i keep tellin' ya!

28:25.537 --> 28:27.539
I need a cave of my own!

28:27.748 --> 28:30.709
Soon enough -- when
our quest is victorious.

28:30.918 --> 28:32.836
Well, sir Peter,
old buddy,

28:33.045 --> 28:35.172
your armies better be worth
their salt.

28:35.380 --> 28:36.464
We need power!

28:36.673 --> 28:38.216
My armies?

28:38.467 --> 28:40.385
Sir Peter has brought
no armies.

28:40.594 --> 28:42.721
What?! No armies?!

28:43.597 --> 28:44.764
Will you please --

28:44.973 --> 28:46.307
what good is he?!

28:46.767 --> 28:48.602
What good is he?!

28:48.977 --> 28:50.812
What good is he?!

28:51.146 --> 28:53.815
Calm down!
Just look at yourself.

28:54.107 --> 28:56.442
Release some gas
at once!

28:56.652 --> 28:58.028
Huh? Oh!

28:58.237 --> 28:59.488
And turn your head!

29:03.367 --> 29:05.285
Extraordinary!

29:05.577 --> 29:07.370
The fiery breath
has something to do

29:07.579 --> 29:10.832
with the dragon's ability
to fly, but what?

29:11.041 --> 29:13.043
Lam certain
you will figure it out.

29:13.252 --> 29:14.836
Smrgol: Help!

29:15.420 --> 29:17.255
Help me!

29:21.343 --> 29:22.761
Uncle smrgol!

29:22.970 --> 29:25.806
He's lost his fire!
Help him, gorbash!

29:51.123 --> 29:52.624
What happened, old friend?

29:53.083 --> 29:55.960
My -- my comrades...

29:56.169 --> 29:57.420
My cronies...

29:57.796 --> 29:59.923
The entire flight...

30:00.132 --> 30:00.924
They all --

30:01.550 --> 30:03.552
all turned against me.

30:03.969 --> 30:06.596
The other dragons?
Why?

30:06.805 --> 30:10.225
Because i-l wouldn't
denounce you and --

30:10.600 --> 30:13.436
and join...Ommadon.

30:13.645 --> 30:16.856
The other dragons
have gone over to ommadon?

30:17.065 --> 30:17.982
Aye.

30:18.608 --> 30:21.611
Aye, he's cast
a spell on 'em all --

30:22.529 --> 30:26.908
a flight of dragons
to protect his crown.

30:48.847 --> 30:51.558
What a strange use for gold.

30:51.767 --> 30:54.770
Because dragons tend
to ignite ordinary bedding,

30:55.145 --> 30:57.355
they must find
a soft metal to sleep on.

30:57.898 --> 31:00.275
And gold proves
most comfortable for them.

31:00.984 --> 31:04.237
Ah, hence the dragon's
need for a hoard.

31:05.906 --> 31:09.618
Perhaps we better continue
this conversation in my study --

31:09.826 --> 31:12.036
less chance
of interruption there.

31:15.332 --> 31:18.793
The last realm of magic --
my own personal dream.

31:19.002 --> 31:20.670
Wow! What a movie show!

31:23.131 --> 31:25.550
Oh, sit down, my son.

31:25.842 --> 31:28.135
I've got lots to explain.

31:32.516 --> 31:36.144
So, <i>that</i> is Peter Dickinson.

31:36.853 --> 31:39.438
That is the pathetic fool

31:39.648 --> 31:44.148
carolinus has enlisted
to steal my crown.

31:44.945 --> 31:46.279
Still...

31:47.656 --> 31:51.618
Antiquity must have had
a reason.

31:52.661 --> 31:54.162
Briag...

31:54.746 --> 31:56.205
Fetch me the fool.

32:07.717 --> 32:10.928
And so, you are the one person
from all the centuries

32:11.138 --> 32:12.764
whom antiquity has chosen.

32:13.014 --> 32:15.766
Because I am
a man of science?

32:15.976 --> 32:16.810
Well, aren't you?

32:17.102 --> 32:19.729
I was at first --
honor student, scholarships,

32:19.938 --> 32:22.273
awards, grants, research --

32:22.816 --> 32:24.526
<i>but how it all bored me!</i>

32:24.776 --> 32:26.444
<i>Who could ponder equations</i>

32:26.653 --> 32:28.988
<i>when he had the chance
to imagine dragons?</i>

32:29.197 --> 32:30.281
<i>So I turned
my back on it all</i>

32:30.490 --> 32:32.742
<i>and started on my book,
"the flight of dragons."</i>

32:33.493 --> 32:36.287
<i>"The flight of dragons."</i>

32:36.997 --> 32:39.666
Yes!
Yes, here it is.

32:40.083 --> 32:42.585
"'The flight of dragons'
by Peter Dickinson."

32:42.794 --> 32:44.086
But...

32:44.296 --> 32:45.922
It's impossible!

32:46.256 --> 32:48.383
That's not even
half finished!

32:48.592 --> 32:49.676
Of course not!

32:49.885 --> 32:52.554
This is my library
of unwritten books!

32:52.762 --> 32:56.098
See -- "beowulf,"
"the idylls of the king,"

32:56.308 --> 32:58.310
"gulliver's travels,"
"the tempest,"

32:58.518 --> 33:00.895
"Alice in wonderland,"
"the wizard of oz."

33:01.146 --> 33:03.022
Incredible.

33:03.648 --> 33:05.858
Nice to know you'll
finish it someday, eh?

33:06.067 --> 33:08.778
Oh! No fair peeking
at the end!

33:09.654 --> 33:11.530
You are unique --

33:12.032 --> 33:14.701
a man with one foot
in the realm of magic

33:14.910 --> 33:16.995
and the other
in the realm of science.

33:18.038 --> 33:21.666
Sir Peter, I present you
with the shield of saturn

33:22.000 --> 33:23.835
and the flute of Olympus.

33:24.294 --> 33:25.837
Sir, I'm no warrior.

33:26.046 --> 33:28.006
I'm awkward, clumsy.

33:29.508 --> 33:31.259
Not anymore, my son,

33:31.468 --> 33:34.721
for I believe you have found
your time and place.

33:35.055 --> 33:37.015
You are too modest,
sir Peter.

33:37.599 --> 33:39.684
Let us toast the quest.

33:39.893 --> 33:41.185
No. No, my dear.

33:41.394 --> 33:43.771
Cider makes evil magic
in the stomach.

33:43.980 --> 33:45.773
Oh, poor father.

33:46.066 --> 33:49.110
You know, I had a professor
with your condition,

33:49.444 --> 33:51.237
but it had nothing
to do with magic.

33:51.488 --> 33:53.406
It was plain stomach ulcers.

33:53.657 --> 33:55.075
Milk was the only thing
that helped.

33:55.700 --> 33:57.660
Milk. Really?

33:58.912 --> 34:03.041
Alas, gorbash has devoured
every cow within 20 miles.

34:03.250 --> 34:06.544
Father, waste a little magic
and change the cider.

34:06.962 --> 34:08.755
This toast is important.

34:09.505 --> 34:10.882
I suppose you're right.

34:11.757 --> 34:15.344
<i>Kala bovina mo!</i>

34:16.137 --> 34:17.346
All: To the quest!

34:18.223 --> 34:19.724
Amazing!

34:22.310 --> 34:25.980
I've tried all kinds of
spells and incantations.

34:26.188 --> 34:29.317
You see, sir Peter,
your science has helped already.

34:39.869 --> 34:41.829
Do you find this
enchanting, sir Peter?

34:42.038 --> 34:44.123
Beyond my wildest dreams.

34:44.666 --> 34:49.166
If all this is just a game,
i wish to play it forever.

34:51.089 --> 34:53.882
I beg you to take this --
a talisman.

34:54.634 --> 34:56.636
Take it,
and may it protect you.

34:57.220 --> 34:59.805
You are my champion,
sir Peter.

35:00.307 --> 35:02.225
Bring me back
the red crown.

35:04.519 --> 35:06.062
[ Roaring 1

35:06.313 --> 35:09.107
aah!

35:10.900 --> 35:13.611
I tell you,
i smell strange dragon!

35:13.820 --> 35:15.863
Look! Terrible!

35:16.781 --> 35:19.950
Briag's capturing
your scientist for ommadon!

35:20.160 --> 35:22.871
Carolinus: And our quest
is over before it starts!

35:23.079 --> 35:25.915
Father! Gorbash!
Do something!

35:26.124 --> 35:27.834
Wait here. Come on.

35:28.043 --> 35:29.627
I'll overtake the swine!

35:29.836 --> 35:31.879
The devil dragon
is too swift.

35:32.088 --> 35:35.299
A removal spell is called for
to bring Peter back.

35:35.508 --> 35:38.010
That takes too long!
Let me do it!

35:54.986 --> 35:59.031
I call on all antiquity
to give me magic enough.

36:00.033 --> 36:01.409
How does it begin?

36:10.418 --> 36:14.422
Oh! Father!
He's dropping sir Peter!

36:21.096 --> 36:24.182
May the rocks
crush your skull!

36:32.607 --> 36:35.067
Oh, the blazes -- <i>kala!</i>

36:50.792 --> 36:52.001
What happened?!

36:52.711 --> 36:53.837
Where's Peter?!

36:54.379 --> 36:55.505
He's gone!

36:56.339 --> 36:57.590
He's gone!

37:03.722 --> 37:06.349
Gorbash, you're releasing
too much fire!

37:06.558 --> 37:08.142
Breathe in! Breathe in!

37:18.570 --> 37:21.698
Smrgol: Come, nephew,
you can pull through.

37:22.240 --> 37:23.157
Keep breathing.

37:24.033 --> 37:26.910
Now, open your eyes.

37:30.081 --> 37:31.082
Yeah.

37:31.332 --> 37:33.250
Yeah, he'll be coming
around soon.

37:33.460 --> 37:35.503
I didn't have time!

37:35.754 --> 37:37.464
The spell was incomplete!

37:38.506 --> 37:40.674
I'm certain we'll find
sir Peter.

37:40.884 --> 37:41.551
Where?

37:41.801 --> 37:45.262
He could be at loathly tower,
Boston, or on the moon,

37:45.472 --> 37:46.556
for all I know.

37:49.684 --> 37:51.102
He's awakening --

37:51.770 --> 37:53.188
right as rain!

37:54.439 --> 37:57.191
By all, that's magic.

37:57.400 --> 38:00.403
Is the dragon
not a wonderful creature?

38:01.112 --> 38:02.571
Open your eyes, boy.

38:02.989 --> 38:06.200
Come on,
come all the way about.

38:07.494 --> 38:09.287
Ahh, ha ha.

38:09.704 --> 38:12.206
It's me, lad,
your uncle.

38:13.333 --> 38:14.834
Don't you recognize me?

38:15.460 --> 38:17.962
Uncle? What?

38:19.964 --> 38:21.256
Melisande!

38:21.466 --> 38:22.925
Iam here, brother.

38:23.468 --> 38:24.719
Brother?

38:25.762 --> 38:26.679
Uh...

38:26.888 --> 38:28.431
W-we kissed.

38:28.890 --> 38:29.891
Kissed?

38:32.227 --> 38:33.353
What is it, child?

38:33.561 --> 38:35.187
Does he know where Peter...

38:35.396 --> 38:37.314
He...He...

38:37.524 --> 38:40.109
He is sir Peter!

38:40.318 --> 38:42.236
Well, of course I'm Peter.

38:42.445 --> 38:45.239
By the beards of antiquity!

38:45.532 --> 38:47.659
I went and merged them!

38:47.909 --> 38:48.534
Merged?

38:48.743 --> 38:51.912
Peter and gorbash are one!

38:52.622 --> 38:56.292
Peter is in gorbash!

38:56.501 --> 38:59.462
Well, blast it, man!
Undo it!

38:59.796 --> 39:01.631
<i>I can't</i> undo
till I find out

39:01.840 --> 39:03.716
what I did
in the first place.

39:03.925 --> 39:07.386
But -- but where is gorbash?

39:07.637 --> 39:10.264
He's still
inside here with me.

39:10.515 --> 39:12.975
I can feel him
in the back of my mind

39:13.184 --> 39:15.019
sleeping soundly right now.

39:15.228 --> 39:17.897
Well, may he rest well
till I figure out

39:18.189 --> 39:19.732
how to separate you.

39:22.068 --> 39:23.235
<i>This can't be</i> a game.

39:23.444 --> 39:27.281
I never invented a rule
to cover a situation like this.

39:43.548 --> 39:46.092
[ Door creaks 1

39:46.593 --> 39:48.219
sir orren Neville-Smythe

39:48.428 --> 39:49.846
at your service!

39:50.346 --> 39:51.680
I've ridden all night.

39:51.931 --> 39:53.265
Before the quest begins,

39:54.017 --> 39:56.310
I hope there's time
for a good hot cup of tea.

39:56.603 --> 39:59.188
Tea? Milk.

40:03.026 --> 40:06.404
"My dearest brothers,
lotagal and solarius,

40:06.613 --> 40:09.407
"today at noon
began the quest

40:09.616 --> 40:13.161
to capture
the red crown of ommadon..."

40:13.369 --> 40:16.955
"...lf the urgency of our
mission is ever questioned,

40:17.248 --> 40:19.875
"yestereve's tragic comedy
is proof enough

40:20.084 --> 40:24.379
"of our waning magic powers,
for a spell went wrong

40:24.631 --> 40:26.424
"and sir Peter
of beacon street

40:26.799 --> 40:29.593
was merged
with my dragon gorbash..."

40:32.263 --> 40:33.973
"...our quest now contains

40:34.182 --> 40:37.143
"one knight,
sir orren Neville-Smythe,

40:37.352 --> 40:41.852
"and one dragon with the mind
and heart of 20th-century man.

40:42.065 --> 40:44.817
"The laws command
that three begin.

40:45.026 --> 40:47.278
"Melisande being
out of the question,

40:47.570 --> 40:51.824
I enlisted the temporary aid
of old smrgol."

40:52.033 --> 40:55.077
I know smrgol is aging
and none too strong,

40:55.286 --> 40:58.414
but I hope carolinus
will gather other allies.

40:58.915 --> 41:00.041
He'll need them.

41:01.542 --> 41:05.587
"...meanwhile, the old dragon
will be able to teach Peter

41:05.838 --> 41:08.215
the ways of his species."

41:11.761 --> 41:14.096
A dragon...

41:14.305 --> 41:17.766
That doesn't know
how to be...A dragon!

41:29.362 --> 41:32.448
Come on out, you
mealy-mouthed little runts!

41:32.699 --> 41:34.200
Is this necessary?

41:34.409 --> 41:35.701
You want to fly,
don't you?

41:36.369 --> 41:38.329
To fly,
you need gemstones.

41:38.663 --> 41:41.874
To get gemstones,
you rob dwarf mines.

41:42.583 --> 41:45.877
Come on out, I say!
And bring gems!

41:46.087 --> 41:47.797
[ Roaring 1

41:48.172 --> 41:50.090
[ sizzling 1

41:57.515 --> 41:59.975
hurry, now,
before we devour you!

42:00.184 --> 42:01.727
You wouldn't really?

42:01.936 --> 42:04.021
Not dwarves, no.

42:04.522 --> 42:06.524
They're all sinewy
and hairy.

42:06.983 --> 42:09.819
The meat you get's not worth
pickin' out of the teeth.

42:11.154 --> 42:12.864
Now, swallow them down.

42:13.072 --> 42:14.364
Not all the way.

42:14.574 --> 42:16.659
Let them find your craw.

42:19.579 --> 42:20.955
Odd sensation.

42:21.164 --> 42:23.541
Never had diamonds
in your craw?

42:23.791 --> 42:24.958
I never had a craw.

42:25.168 --> 42:26.377
They help grind up

42:26.586 --> 42:28.879
the white fire rock
when you eat it.

42:29.172 --> 42:30.214
That's limestone.

42:30.423 --> 42:33.968
A puny man word
if I ever heard it. Eat.

42:35.344 --> 42:37.846
You'd wear down your teeth
grinding this stuff,

42:38.056 --> 42:40.600
so you swallow it
in chunks.

42:40.808 --> 42:42.893
Wiggle it around
with the gemstones

42:43.102 --> 42:44.478
till they're pulverized.

42:44.687 --> 42:47.606
It's like birds use grit
to grind seed.

42:47.815 --> 42:50.526
Yeah, but don't talk
with your mouth full!

42:52.987 --> 42:54.780
What's all this
to do with flying?

42:55.490 --> 42:59.285
It makes the fire in your belly
that gives you lift.

42:59.577 --> 43:03.956
Hmm, limestone
is high in calcium.

43:04.373 --> 43:06.875
Calcium, when mixed
with stomach acids,

43:07.126 --> 43:08.710
would form hydrogen.

43:09.587 --> 43:11.422
Hydrogen is lighter
than air,

43:11.631 --> 43:13.174
thus giving the lift
you talk about --

43:13.382 --> 43:14.925
something like a blimp.

43:15.134 --> 43:16.260
What?

43:17.470 --> 43:20.723
You got fire inside you
when you go up.

43:21.015 --> 43:22.808
That's all you need
to know.

43:23.017 --> 43:24.476
No, that's not logical.

43:24.685 --> 43:26.770
How could my ribs
contain fire?

43:27.605 --> 43:29.648
If I could only visualize --

43:29.857 --> 43:34.357
oh, for cryin' out loud --
visualize!

43:35.822 --> 43:36.447
I know.

43:38.866 --> 43:40.409
Man, this is great!

43:41.160 --> 43:43.662
Now, as you explain,
I'll make a diagram.

43:43.871 --> 43:45.247
Of all the...

43:47.166 --> 43:49.751
Well, I'm doin' it
for carolinus.

43:51.045 --> 43:53.464
You see, we got
this great, like --

43:54.549 --> 43:58.719
like a honeycomb of bone
and muscle inside us.

43:59.929 --> 44:01.096
Something like this?

44:01.305 --> 44:03.265
Aye. Aye, that's it.

44:03.474 --> 44:06.143
Compartments we can
expand and contract.

44:06.352 --> 44:09.063
And when we expand,
the hydrogen --

44:09.272 --> 44:11.357
I mean, dragon fire,
as it were --

44:11.566 --> 44:14.110
expands and makes us
lighter than air,

44:14.318 --> 44:16.528
and up we go!

44:20.575 --> 44:22.451
Hey, how do I get down?

44:22.785 --> 44:25.829
Blow it out -- belch!

44:26.247 --> 44:28.958
Yes! Close the valves
and expel gas to come down.

44:29.167 --> 44:30.751
Well, go ahead.

44:34.005 --> 44:37.299
Turn your head,
you dummy!

44:37.717 --> 44:40.678
Wh-- whoa! Ooh! Uh!

44:42.597 --> 44:44.807
But I wonder why
it comes out as fire?

44:45.016 --> 44:49.516
Because we're dragons,
and dragons breathe fire!

44:49.854 --> 44:52.106
Yes, but what makes
the ignition?

44:52.315 --> 44:54.317
The Thor thimble, fool.

44:54.942 --> 44:56.944
Look, in the roof
of your mouth --

44:57.195 --> 44:59.739
feel it --
feel it with your tongue.

44:59.947 --> 45:01.949
Mmm...Yes!

45:02.158 --> 45:04.076
It feels like a thimble.

45:04.327 --> 45:05.578
Ow! Ow! Ow!

45:05.995 --> 45:07.663
Mmm! Electricity!

45:08.331 --> 45:12.293
The electricity
ignites the hydrogen.

45:12.543 --> 45:16.713
Dragon fire, dragon flight --
it all makes perfect sense!

45:16.923 --> 45:20.009
Oh! Oh, what I wouldn't give
for my typewriter!

45:20.218 --> 45:22.845
Ah, shut up
and eat your limestone.

45:29.977 --> 45:31.770
Sir orren: I must say, lancer,

45:31.979 --> 45:35.148
this is the loneliest quest
I've <i>ever</i> undertaken.

45:35.358 --> 45:39.858
Still, I suppose it necessary
that sir Peter learn how to fly.

45:40.279 --> 45:41.863
Nice chap -- what?

45:42.073 --> 45:45.868
Soon it will be nightfall --
ommadon's hours.

45:46.077 --> 45:48.954
Hmm. I'd best summon them.

45:56.087 --> 46:00.174
Hark! Hear that?
Aye, he's calling us.

46:00.716 --> 46:02.050
Shall we go back on foot,

46:02.260 --> 46:05.763
or do you think you
can manage a short flight?

46:05.972 --> 46:06.764
I can try.

46:06.973 --> 46:08.474
Expand...

46:08.683 --> 46:10.142
Feel the lift.

46:14.146 --> 46:18.358
Now, propel yourself
this way.

46:21.320 --> 46:24.614
Use your wings to steer --
to navigate,

46:24.824 --> 46:26.325
and to keep your balance.

46:28.995 --> 46:29.912
Whoo!

46:31.414 --> 46:33.499
Look, I know you
don't like comparisons,

46:33.708 --> 46:36.168
but this is exactly
how a 747 does it.

46:36.377 --> 46:37.628
I love it!

47:11.245 --> 47:14.498
I say, old chap, bad show.

47:14.707 --> 47:16.542
I'm okay, I'm okay.

47:16.751 --> 47:19.670
Ahh, you blew
all your fire.

47:19.879 --> 47:23.048
You won't have
any lift again until dawn.

47:23.257 --> 47:26.343
Well, you certainly don't
want to chance night flight.

47:26.552 --> 47:28.053
We'd best make camp.

47:28.262 --> 47:29.805
Aye.

47:30.014 --> 47:32.850
I'm going to miss
my bed of gold.

47:37.563 --> 47:38.689
[Growling 1

47:44.403 --> 47:46.238
care to join me,
sir Peter?

47:47.156 --> 47:49.741
No, I suppose not.

47:49.950 --> 47:53.328
All big-dragoned as you are --
must be most annoying.

47:54.914 --> 47:56.415
Ahh.

47:58.000 --> 48:02.379
I have a longing to eat a cow.
I can't believe it --

48:02.588 --> 48:06.300
an entire cow --
hooves, tail, bones, ears --

48:06.509 --> 48:07.343
the whole thing!

48:07.551 --> 48:10.637
Yes, well, to each his own.

48:10.846 --> 48:14.182
You know, I shouldn't
really like you so much --

48:14.433 --> 48:18.353
all that business
with melisande and all.

48:18.562 --> 48:21.314
If it weren't
for this dragon business,

48:21.524 --> 48:22.358
the laws of chivalry

48:22.566 --> 48:24.734
would force me to challenge
you to a joust.

48:24.944 --> 48:27.821
I hope we never
come to that, sir orren.

48:28.030 --> 48:30.198
I do love her
with all my heart --

48:30.449 --> 48:34.949
her purity, grace, innocence,
and title are an inspiration.

48:36.539 --> 48:37.540
Have you known her long?

48:37.790 --> 48:39.416
Since she was five.

48:39.625 --> 48:42.002
Oddly enough,
you brought us together.

48:42.294 --> 48:43.086
Me?

48:43.295 --> 48:45.880
Well, gorbash did.

48:46.132 --> 48:47.758
You see,
about a dozen years ago,

48:47.967 --> 48:51.178
I was mucking about
in ommadon's red-devil realm

48:51.387 --> 48:53.097
<i>or whatever it's called</i> --

48:54.098 --> 48:56.600
<i>some sort of quest</i> --

48:56.809 --> 48:59.561
<i>returning from
a crusade, perhaps.</i>

49:01.564 --> 49:04.817
<i>I suddenly spied
a rather smashing sight --</i>

49:05.651 --> 49:08.236
<i>a nest of dragon's eggs.</i>

49:09.405 --> 49:13.242
<i>Well, I was about to do
a charcoal sketch</i>

49:13.534 --> 49:15.577
<i>when who showed up
but briag...</i>

49:15.828 --> 49:17.788
[ Roaring 1

49:29.049 --> 49:31.676
<i>...and he began to sup
on the next generation,</i>

49:31.886 --> 49:32.970
<i>as it were.</i>

49:33.971 --> 49:35.931
Hold and get ye hither,

49:36.182 --> 49:38.184
or prepare to die!

49:38.392 --> 49:41.269
[Growling 1

49:47.234 --> 49:49.152
aaahhhh!

49:50.070 --> 49:52.989
<i>Got a -- got a good blow,
if I do say so.</i>

49:53.199 --> 49:55.868
<i>Must have been half an hour
before I opened my eyes.</i>

49:56.285 --> 49:57.327
<i>But when I did...</i>

49:59.580 --> 50:03.458
<i>...l found he'd decimated
the entire litter, save one.</i>

50:04.043 --> 50:06.962
<i>Well, it seemed a shame
to die for an egg,</i>

50:07.338 --> 50:09.089
<i>but I'd made the challenge --</i>

50:09.298 --> 50:11.550
<i>the laws of chivalry
and all that, you know.</i>

50:30.361 --> 50:32.654
<i>Bit of this,
bit of that,</i>

50:32.863 --> 50:35.073
<i>he had me, I had him.</i>

50:38.702 --> 50:40.495
<i>Couldn't open his mouth,
you see?</i>

50:40.829 --> 50:42.664
<i>The gases built up
inside.</i>

50:42.915 --> 50:44.791
<i>And I took
a bit of a chance</i>

50:45.000 --> 50:47.168
<i>and let him devour
my metal gauntlet.</i>

50:47.920 --> 50:49.546
<i>In less than a moment,</i>

50:49.797 --> 50:51.465
<i>it touched Thor's thimble --</i>

50:52.049 --> 50:54.551
<i>bit of an internal explosion,
i fear.</i>

50:59.848 --> 51:01.850
[ Roaring 1

51:07.690 --> 51:09.149
<i>almost killed him.</i>

51:09.358 --> 51:10.567
<i>Wished it had.</i>

51:10.776 --> 51:12.402
<i>He didn't like it
at all.</i>

51:12.945 --> 51:15.447
<i>Took him seven years
to recuperate</i> --

51:15.656 --> 51:17.324
<i>quite a bit for a dragon.</i>

51:17.616 --> 51:20.118
<i>Hates me, needless to say.</i>

51:20.744 --> 51:23.455
<i>Anyway, I'd saved the egg.</i>

51:43.017 --> 51:46.353
<i>Cute little fellow --
awkward and helpless.</i>

51:46.729 --> 51:49.690
<i>Named him gorbash
in honor of the contest.</i>

51:50.107 --> 51:54.569
<i>It was rather gory, and i
did geta bit bashed about.</i>

51:54.778 --> 51:57.363
<i>Get it -- gory, bashed?</i>

51:57.823 --> 51:59.825
<i>Hence, gorbash.</i>

52:00.701 --> 52:02.953
<i>Popped in on
my old friend, carolinus.</i>

52:03.203 --> 52:05.788
<i>Found he'd adopted
an enchanting daughter.</i>

52:06.498 --> 52:08.041
<i>Gave her the little dragon.</i>

52:10.127 --> 52:12.462
<i>Old smrgol said
he'd be like an uncle --</i>

52:12.880 --> 52:14.882
<i>teach him
the way of dragons.</i>

52:15.382 --> 52:18.009
<i>I made a vow to fall
in love with melisande</i> --

52:18.385 --> 52:19.928
<i>when she was old enough,
of course.</i>

52:22.222 --> 52:23.514
Kept the vow.

52:25.225 --> 52:27.060
Dashed lot of good
it did me.

52:28.228 --> 52:29.687
And now she likes me.

52:30.189 --> 52:32.274
<i>I did</i> write the rules
to this game, you know.

52:32.858 --> 52:34.818
<i>No, I mean,
I'm really quite sorry.</i>

52:35.027 --> 52:37.070
<i>Not at all, old chap!</i>

52:37.321 --> 52:39.656
<i>Feel lucky
she's attracted to you.</i>

52:41.408 --> 52:42.784
Blast! It's fading!

52:43.535 --> 52:45.620
Is all my magic spent?

52:45.871 --> 52:47.372
Father, rest.

52:47.581 --> 52:49.583
But I thought I heard
just as it faded...

52:49.833 --> 52:50.792
Heard what?

52:51.001 --> 52:52.460
A chattering sound

52:52.670 --> 52:55.714
which could indicate
something so terrible --

52:56.548 --> 52:58.383
no, it's impossible --

52:58.592 --> 53:00.051
not in the forest.

53:00.260 --> 53:03.930
And yet, I wouldn't put it
past ommadon to --

53:04.473 --> 53:07.267
see! See, blast you!

53:07.476 --> 53:08.768
[Vibrating 1

53:08.977 --> 53:10.645
<i>gentle, sweet brother.</i>

53:11.230 --> 53:13.941
My magic's not spent,
just confused.

53:14.149 --> 53:15.650
I want the forest, not --

53:15.859 --> 53:17.861
<i>I am speaking to you
through my magic,</i>

53:18.070 --> 53:19.738
<i>which is none too strong.</i>

53:19.988 --> 53:21.406
<i>Let me be quick.</i>

53:21.657 --> 53:25.535
<i>Melisande has powers
to see over distance.</i>

53:25.744 --> 53:27.245
Father, let me try.

53:28.664 --> 53:30.290
Very well, my dear.

53:31.041 --> 53:32.417
Close your eyes.

53:33.293 --> 53:34.627
Easy, now.

53:35.254 --> 53:37.214
You will see gormly forest.

53:38.215 --> 53:41.718
Our friends, defenders
of the magic realm...

53:42.344 --> 53:45.138
Yes. Yes.

53:45.347 --> 53:47.557
Smrgol is asleep.

53:47.808 --> 53:49.726
Peter and sir orren
are speaking.

53:50.018 --> 53:50.852
[ <i>Rattling</i> 1

53:51.061 --> 53:54.230
oh, father,
i <i>do</i> hear that sound!

53:54.481 --> 53:55.773
It's terrifying!

53:57.317 --> 53:59.485
We'd best follow
the old fellow's example.

54:00.028 --> 54:02.321
We'll be nearing the
devil's realm by the morrow,

54:02.531 --> 54:04.533
and we'll need
all the rest we can get.

54:04.867 --> 54:06.159
Do you hear...

54:06.410 --> 54:09.454
Strange --
like some insects.

54:11.415 --> 54:13.583
Ah, crickets, no doubt.

54:14.293 --> 54:16.753
Seems to make
my whole head tingle.

54:16.962 --> 54:19.172
Yes, it is rather annoying.

54:20.340 --> 54:21.382
<i>It couldn't</i> be!

54:22.050 --> 54:23.676
They only appear
at the seashore!

54:24.052 --> 54:24.719
What?

54:24.928 --> 54:26.095
Impossible, I tell you!

54:26.555 --> 54:28.473
Why are you yelling at me?!

54:28.724 --> 54:30.559
You stupid, slobbering beast!

54:31.101 --> 54:32.477
Don't you know
sandmurks?!

54:32.686 --> 54:35.772
Why, you idiotic,
tin-coated goody-two-shoes!

54:38.692 --> 54:41.236
Peter,
it's the brain fryer!

54:41.612 --> 54:43.363
Blot out the cursed sound!

54:43.614 --> 54:46.325
Sandmurks --
try to understand!

54:49.536 --> 54:51.287
Hold, sir Peter,
i beg you!

54:51.580 --> 54:52.914
Lt's the sandmurks --

54:53.165 --> 54:55.750
horrid little creatures
who attack by the millions!

54:56.084 --> 54:59.087
Their chirping drives
all living things insane!

54:59.379 --> 55:02.423
Your brain will burn
till you die!

55:02.633 --> 55:04.092
Ow!

55:05.177 --> 55:07.179
I did it to bring you
to your senses!

55:07.387 --> 55:10.765
Now, listen -- fly!
Fly away before it's too late!

55:11.016 --> 55:12.851
Can't -- I can't!

55:13.060 --> 55:15.687
Used up all my lift
in the crash before!

55:16.939 --> 55:17.689
Look!

55:17.981 --> 55:18.898
I see them!

55:19.107 --> 55:20.358
Clear your mind!

55:20.567 --> 55:23.319
Think anything --
a poem, a song!

55:23.654 --> 55:25.280
Don't let them
burn your mind!

55:25.656 --> 55:26.865
Aaahhhh!

55:37.084 --> 55:41.584
N' I come from Alabama
with a banjo on my -- aah! H'

55:42.130 --> 55:46.630
n' I'm goin' to Louisiana,
my true lo-- my true... <i>H'</i>

55:46.885 --> 55:48.469
aaahhhh!

55:48.679 --> 55:49.721
No!

55:49.930 --> 55:52.223
N' ...For to see --
for to see... h'

55:52.432 --> 55:53.516
help me!

55:53.892 --> 55:56.227
H' it rained all night... <i>H'</i>

55:57.396 --> 56:00.065
the noise!
I cannot stand it!

56:00.274 --> 56:01.942
Melisande,
come to your senses!

56:02.150 --> 56:05.111
You killed
my mother and father!

56:05.320 --> 56:07.447
You blamed it
on demons, but you --

56:07.656 --> 56:08.990
melisande!

56:09.992 --> 56:12.411
[ Howling 1

56:19.835 --> 56:21.795
Dickinson:
Aahhh-aah-aah-aah!

56:22.004 --> 56:24.798
N' oh! Susanna,
don't you cry-y-y-y-y h'

56:25.090 --> 56:26.966
h' come from alabam-a h'

56:27.175 --> 56:31.596
aaaaahhhhhhhh!

56:31.805 --> 56:34.390
N' cuckoo, cuckoo bird,
sing, sing h'

56:34.683 --> 56:37.018
ii sing, cuckoo,
sing, cuckoo ii'

56:37.269 --> 56:40.480
aaaahhhhhh!

56:48.363 --> 56:49.989
Aaah!

56:57.706 --> 56:58.415
[ Barking 1

57:01.293 --> 57:03.128
[ screeching 1

57:11.094 --> 57:11.928
[growling 1

57:27.069 --> 57:28.278
what?

57:28.487 --> 57:31.198
They've --
th ey've retreated!

57:31.406 --> 57:34.659
Thank heaven.
Thank heaven.

57:39.414 --> 57:43.042
Oh, my child, what
have I allowed to happen?

57:43.251 --> 57:46.170
Have they robbed you
of all your senses?

57:46.380 --> 57:48.632
Will you sleep like this
forever?

57:49.132 --> 57:52.260
Oh, my darling,
darling child.

57:52.469 --> 57:54.304
[Sobbing 1

58:02.479 --> 58:03.938
hold, cur!

58:04.272 --> 58:06.315
Not one step further!

58:06.817 --> 58:09.528
Is this the thanks I get?

58:10.362 --> 58:12.614
Gorbash, old friend,

58:13.073 --> 58:15.492
you look like
you've seen a ghost.

58:17.327 --> 58:19.245
Matter of fact,
maybe you have.

58:21.873 --> 58:24.083
Who's laughing --

58:24.376 --> 58:27.128
making such
a confounding racket?

58:27.879 --> 58:30.631
I haven't slept a wink
all night.

58:31.091 --> 58:32.842
Missed my gold and --

58:34.386 --> 58:37.597
arak, good old boy...

58:38.223 --> 58:40.266
I thought you were dead.

58:40.475 --> 58:41.225
You know him?

58:41.435 --> 58:43.437
Know him?
Of course I know him.

58:43.645 --> 58:46.564
Lt's arak, a friend
of the family --

58:46.773 --> 58:49.025
like a big brother to you.

58:49.234 --> 58:50.860
What's the matter, gorbash?

58:51.361 --> 58:53.696
Did the sandmurks steal
your memory?

58:54.448 --> 58:58.118
Sandmurks?
Were there sandmurks here?

58:59.161 --> 59:02.205
Nonsense.
They live by the sea.

59:06.084 --> 59:09.587
Smrgol, you could always sleep
through anything.

59:10.297 --> 59:11.965
The whole trick with sandmurks

59:12.174 --> 59:14.634
is to get the big one --
the queen.

59:14.843 --> 59:16.261
The others are brainless
without her.

59:16.470 --> 59:20.970
Arak, you're supposed to be
dead, killed,

59:21.600 --> 59:24.811
dragged out to sea
by a giant squid.

59:25.854 --> 59:26.980
Quite right.

59:27.939 --> 59:30.399
<i>I woke up underwater.</i>

59:30.609 --> 59:32.235
Awaken, brave arak.

59:32.527 --> 59:35.238
I am solarius,
lord of this realm,

59:35.489 --> 59:37.449
and I can restore you.

59:37.699 --> 59:39.033
Why?

59:40.118 --> 59:42.745
Do I live once more?

59:42.954 --> 59:46.832
No. You are drowned.
But I have a task for you.

59:47.042 --> 59:49.961
Accomplish it,
and you will live again.

59:51.088 --> 59:53.173
Ommadon has enlisted
the sandmurks

59:53.381 --> 59:55.091
to defeat carolinus.

59:55.300 --> 59:57.093
You must destroy them.

59:57.302 --> 59:59.512
Give me life, and I will.

59:59.721 --> 01:00:01.180
After the task,

01:00:01.389 --> 01:00:04.850
for nothing living can withstand
their terrible cries.

01:00:05.060 --> 01:00:09.105
Destroy them, and you will start
to breathe once more.

01:00:09.481 --> 01:00:11.357
It seemed like a fair bargain.

01:00:11.983 --> 01:00:16.112
I did my part, and as soon
as queen sandmurk was gone,

01:00:16.321 --> 01:00:17.071
I started to breathe,

01:00:17.280 --> 01:00:19.657
so solarius
obviously did his.

01:00:22.994 --> 01:00:25.621
Good old gorbash.

01:00:25.997 --> 01:00:28.833
What times we used to have.

01:00:29.209 --> 01:00:30.877
Arak, i-I've got to explain.

01:00:31.169 --> 01:00:32.503
Explain later!

01:00:32.879 --> 01:00:35.172
We have the sun
and must press on.

01:00:35.382 --> 01:00:36.633
Forward!

01:00:36.925 --> 01:00:40.929
To the realm of the red death
and the red crown of ommadon!

01:01:02.284 --> 01:01:03.368
You have friends about?

01:01:03.577 --> 01:01:04.661
A female.

01:01:04.995 --> 01:01:08.540
Trouble --
she's protecting her cubs.

01:01:09.040 --> 01:01:09.707
Wait.

01:01:12.752 --> 01:01:13.669
If he's not careful,

01:01:13.879 --> 01:01:16.381
he'll have a whole family
on his hands.

01:01:16.965 --> 01:01:21.052
I can't say I'd mind the chance
to rest, though.

01:01:24.472 --> 01:01:25.806
What the blazes?

01:01:26.016 --> 01:01:29.019
Blazes --
we've gotta get loose.

01:01:29.394 --> 01:01:30.853
It's dragon rose.

01:01:34.191 --> 01:01:35.192
Hold your breath.

01:01:35.692 --> 01:01:37.151
Don't breathe.

01:01:38.862 --> 01:01:41.406
Ugly, foul smell.

01:01:41.781 --> 01:01:43.532
Those goganflowers.

01:01:51.750 --> 01:01:54.127
Can't...Stay...Awake.

01:02:01.468 --> 01:02:03.219
[Sniffing 1

01:02:03.470 --> 01:02:06.139
not a wolf for miles.

01:02:25.617 --> 01:02:28.661
Well, whoever is doing
the shooting, god bless him.

01:02:28.870 --> 01:02:31.080
He certainly can handle
a longbow.

01:02:31.289 --> 01:02:32.957
I trust he's on our side.

01:02:34.709 --> 01:02:35.626
There he is.

01:02:35.877 --> 01:02:37.461
Good show, man.

01:02:37.963 --> 01:02:39.714
I bow to such expertise

01:02:39.923 --> 01:02:42.842
and doff this helmet
to a better man than l.

01:02:43.093 --> 01:02:45.428
And <i>I</i> doff my cap to you,
sir orren.

01:02:45.637 --> 01:02:47.680
By all that's holy!

01:02:48.932 --> 01:02:50.892
I am Danielle of the woodland,
sir orren.

01:02:51.184 --> 01:02:52.268
You know me?

01:02:52.519 --> 01:02:54.479
My father sang
of your exploits.

01:02:54.771 --> 01:02:56.606
You have always been
a hero of mine.

01:02:56.815 --> 01:03:00.235
Oh, too good to be true.

01:03:00.443 --> 01:03:01.193
Hush!

01:03:01.403 --> 01:03:03.029
You must forgive
the wood elves.

01:03:03.238 --> 01:03:06.157
They are petty outlaws
but good at their jobs.

01:03:06.533 --> 01:03:09.827
And this is their leader,
giles of the treetops.

01:03:10.495 --> 01:03:11.537
For shame.

01:03:11.746 --> 01:03:13.330
We saw the dragons.

01:03:13.707 --> 01:03:15.792
We thought they were
ommadon's raiders.

01:03:17.502 --> 01:03:21.088
A thousand pardons, sir orren.
Had we but known --

01:03:21.548 --> 01:03:24.175
oh, think nothing of it,
little fellow.

01:03:24.676 --> 01:03:27.637
The way things are nowadays,
we all get a bit mucked up.

01:03:28.263 --> 01:03:29.681
Get your men down
from the trees

01:03:29.889 --> 01:03:33.183
and awaken the dragons.
Hurry, now.

01:03:34.144 --> 01:03:37.355
Whatever your quest is,
i should be honored to join.

01:03:37.564 --> 01:03:42.064
Well, it's a bit unusual,
but, speaking for myself,

01:03:42.527 --> 01:03:43.694
I should be honored --

01:03:43.903 --> 01:03:46.113
nay, delighted --
to have you.

01:03:46.656 --> 01:03:49.700
I assure you my skills
will prove most useful.

01:03:53.705 --> 01:03:56.040
<i>Melisande: Danielle
has joined them, father,</i>

01:03:56.708 --> 01:03:59.711
<i>and giles,
the elfin outlaw.</i>

01:04:00.879 --> 01:04:02.463
<i>Night is falling,</i>

01:04:03.298 --> 01:04:05.758
<i>and they are but a day away</i>

01:04:06.468 --> 01:04:08.970
<i>from the realm of ommadon.</i>

01:04:13.141 --> 01:04:14.225
Looks like an inn.

01:04:14.434 --> 01:04:17.728
Hellsway -- last outpost
of civilization

01:04:17.937 --> 01:04:19.939
before the realm
of the red death.

01:04:20.148 --> 01:04:24.648
Arak: And beyond that wall,
all is ommadon's.

01:04:25.362 --> 01:04:27.238
Peter: There seems to be
a castle guarding the gate.

01:04:27.614 --> 01:04:30.491
Aye...Gormlykeep,

01:04:30.867 --> 01:04:33.494
the tollhouse
on the way to Hades,

01:04:34.162 --> 01:04:37.748
with a giant ogre
as tollkeeper.

01:04:38.083 --> 01:04:40.418
The ogre of gormlykeep?

01:04:40.919 --> 01:04:42.670
I've heard tell of him.

01:04:43.296 --> 01:04:47.758
A lumbering, 3-eyed giant
as big as a house.

01:04:48.510 --> 01:04:51.721
Press on -- the hellsway inn.

01:04:51.930 --> 01:04:54.933
A good bed and some hospitality
will be welcome tonight.

01:05:03.233 --> 01:05:04.692
Innkeeper!

01:05:04.901 --> 01:05:06.402
Innkeeper, I say!

01:05:06.611 --> 01:05:08.696
At your service,
sir orren.

01:05:08.905 --> 01:05:11.574
How are my friends doing
below?

01:05:11.783 --> 01:05:13.326
I will look to them.

01:05:13.535 --> 01:05:16.579
I do not usually allow
dragons in my cellars,

01:05:16.788 --> 01:05:17.872
but for you --

01:05:18.164 --> 01:05:21.167
who are those four
somber spoilsports?

01:05:21.376 --> 01:05:23.961
Merchants from ommadon's realm.

01:05:24.212 --> 01:05:26.297
You allow ommadon's swine?!

01:05:26.506 --> 01:05:29.967
Shh! My inn
is between two worlds.

01:05:30.176 --> 01:05:31.760
I cannot take sides.

01:05:31.970 --> 01:05:34.263
Well, <i>I</i> don't like 'em!

01:05:34.472 --> 01:05:36.849
I'll see to the dragons
downstairs.

01:05:45.108 --> 01:05:46.484
On to ommadon.

01:05:52.574 --> 01:05:54.659
More wine?

01:05:55.326 --> 01:05:57.119
Wine not?

01:06:03.626 --> 01:06:06.211
This isn't wine.
It's mead...

01:06:07.005 --> 01:06:08.506
But not bad.

01:06:09.799 --> 01:06:13.928
Peter, how'd that
"beacon street" song go again?

01:06:14.679 --> 01:06:17.473
H' I came from Louisiana <i>h'</i>

01:06:17.682 --> 01:06:20.476
h' with a banjo on my knee <i>h'</i>

01:06:20.685 --> 01:06:23.479
<i>h' oh'. Susanna n'</i>

01:06:23.771 --> 01:06:26.315
h' oh, don't you cry for me <i>h'</i>

01:06:26.524 --> 01:06:28.817
h' I've gone to Alabama h'

01:06:29.110 --> 01:06:30.986
h' with a banjo on my knee <i>h'</i>

01:06:31.196 --> 01:06:33.740
n' pluck-a pluck-a
pluck-a pluck-a n'

01:06:34.365 --> 01:06:36.200
I am ruined!

01:06:38.786 --> 01:06:42.498
Those dragons -- they've
devoured over 100 hams,

01:06:42.790 --> 01:06:47.290
60 cheeses, and at least
30 barrels of my finest mead.

01:06:47.962 --> 01:06:51.173
Tut, tut.
You will be well paid.

01:06:51.466 --> 01:06:53.509
Dragons have gold,
you know.

01:06:53.968 --> 01:06:55.177
They have it with them?

01:06:55.637 --> 01:06:58.056
You will be paid eventually.

01:06:58.264 --> 01:06:59.431
My father told me,

01:06:59.641 --> 01:07:03.019
"never extend credit
to a dragon."

01:07:03.436 --> 01:07:07.106
Shh. Too late
for such caterwaulings --

01:07:07.398 --> 01:07:10.692
too late,
for the morrow brings --

01:07:10.985 --> 01:07:12.695
[yawns 1

01:07:12.904 --> 01:07:16.449
your rooms are ready.
Will you finally to bed?

01:07:16.783 --> 01:07:18.493
Aye, good innkeeper.

01:07:18.785 --> 01:07:21.287
For we may not see
another night.

01:07:22.914 --> 01:07:25.041
I'll show you the way.

01:07:27.001 --> 01:07:29.294
<i>Melisande:
And, lo, they sleep,</i>

01:07:29.671 --> 01:07:33.257
<i>an all-too-brief surcease,
well-earned.</i>

01:07:34.092 --> 01:07:35.968
<i>And but for the watchful moon</i>

01:07:36.177 --> 01:07:39.471
<i>keeping her vigil o'er
the slumbering countryside,</i>

01:07:39.681 --> 01:07:41.391
<i>all is still.</i>

01:07:43.560 --> 01:07:44.477
Aaaaah!

01:07:44.686 --> 01:07:45.978
What is it, child?

01:07:46.437 --> 01:07:47.563
Something looms --

01:07:47.855 --> 01:07:49.940
huge, terrifying,

01:07:50.400 --> 01:07:54.362
with two mad eyes
where three once were!

01:07:54.571 --> 01:07:55.947
Carolinus:
The ogre.

01:07:56.155 --> 01:07:59.241
Ommadon has sent
the ogre of gormlykeep.

01:08:17.801 --> 01:08:19.386
Smrgol, look!

01:08:19.595 --> 01:08:24.095
Hmm?
Ach, what a terrible mess.

01:08:24.767 --> 01:08:25.684
Did we --

01:08:25.893 --> 01:08:27.685
don't -- don't admit
anything.

01:08:27.895 --> 01:08:28.854
Look!

01:08:29.689 --> 01:08:32.692
The innkeeper --
murdered.

01:08:32.899 --> 01:08:33.984
It's horrible.

01:08:35.903 --> 01:08:37.821
I smell ogre.

01:08:38.531 --> 01:08:40.658
Giles: Help! Over here!

01:08:43.953 --> 01:08:44.995
Giles, are you all right?

01:08:45.330 --> 01:08:47.497
I'm near parboiled
to a fare-thee-well,

01:08:47.874 --> 01:08:50.084
but I'd sooner be cooked
than crushed by that thing.

01:08:50.460 --> 01:08:51.627
Tell me what happened, man.

01:08:51.877 --> 01:08:53.962
I hid in the soup
when I first heard him.

01:08:54.296 --> 01:08:55.423
He reached in the window

01:08:55.631 --> 01:08:58.426
and took Danielle and sir orren
from where they lay.

01:09:13.816 --> 01:09:14.858
Then off he goes.

01:09:15.234 --> 01:09:15.984
Where to?

01:09:16.194 --> 01:09:18.654
The dungeon at gormlykeep,
no doubt.

01:09:19.029 --> 01:09:21.823
There they'll hold 'em
till ommadon decides

01:09:22.033 --> 01:09:24.535
what foul deed
to perform on 'em.

01:09:24.743 --> 01:09:25.828
Oh, no.

01:09:26.912 --> 01:09:28.622
A fat lot of good <i>I</i> am
to this quest,

01:09:28.831 --> 01:09:31.457
overcome by the sandmurks
and trapped by the elves' net

01:09:31.667 --> 01:09:33.544
and in a stupor
when the ogre attacks.

01:09:33.752 --> 01:09:36.796
Now, now, Peter,
you've got a job to do,

01:09:37.006 --> 01:09:38.298
and you'll do it.

01:09:38.508 --> 01:09:39.216
What's that?

01:09:39.425 --> 01:09:43.136
Take the ogre of gormlykeep.

01:09:47.684 --> 01:09:50.560
Let me tell you something
about how to fight ogres.

01:09:50.770 --> 01:09:52.270
- Are you listening?
- Yes.

01:09:52.479 --> 01:09:56.817
Good. The first thing to know
is about the bones in an ogre.

01:09:57.026 --> 01:09:57.818
They're thick.

01:09:58.277 --> 01:10:01.863
See, an ogre's arms and legs
are mainly bone.

01:10:02.073 --> 01:10:04.158
That's why biting is no use.

01:10:04.659 --> 01:10:08.371
And their flesh don't burn,
so save your fire.

01:10:08.579 --> 01:10:10.706
If this were my game
and I faced these odds,

01:10:10.915 --> 01:10:13.542
I'd just fold up the board
and put it on a shelf.

01:10:14.627 --> 01:10:16.712
Uh, please continue.

01:10:19.257 --> 01:10:21.133
Let's see -- hopefully
throw him over a cliff.

01:10:21.342 --> 01:10:23.260
If no cliff, go for
the throat or stomach.

01:10:23.511 --> 01:10:24.470
Never let him get a grip.

01:10:24.679 --> 01:10:28.808
Hmm.
I-I'd take him myself,

01:10:29.016 --> 01:10:31.226
but age has got to me.

01:10:31.436 --> 01:10:32.728
I know, sir.

01:10:33.771 --> 01:10:36.231
- You mean I show it?!
- No, sir!

01:10:37.233 --> 01:10:39.944
Don't tell anybody
what I just confessed.

01:10:40.778 --> 01:10:42.488
Ahh, there it is...

01:10:43.531 --> 01:10:45.157
Gormlykeep.

01:10:50.496 --> 01:10:53.040
You go back in there
and hide in the brush.

01:10:53.458 --> 01:10:55.751
We'll need the horse
when we free them.

01:10:57.712 --> 01:10:59.213
Now call him out.

01:10:59.964 --> 01:11:01.173
Give him the challenge.

01:11:01.382 --> 01:11:03.300
Uh, what's his name?

01:11:03.968 --> 01:11:08.468
It don't matter with an ogre.
"Hey, you" will suffice.

01:11:09.348 --> 01:11:11.600
Hey, you!
Come on out and fight!

01:11:19.358 --> 01:11:22.986
Go to it, lad!
Go to it! Now!

01:11:48.387 --> 01:11:49.846
<i>Charge him. Hit his chest.</i>

01:11:50.056 --> 01:11:53.392
<i>Knock him over the wall.
Strength -- give me strength!</i>

01:11:53.601 --> 01:11:55.519
No, lad! No!

01:11:55.728 --> 01:11:57.312
What are you doing?!

01:12:03.319 --> 01:12:06.280
Oh, lad, no.

01:12:06.864 --> 01:12:09.032
You let him
get a grip on you.

01:12:15.581 --> 01:12:18.166
Oh, blazes!

01:12:19.168 --> 01:12:20.669
Hey, hey, you!

01:12:22.213 --> 01:12:24.423
Let that schoolboy go!

01:12:40.273 --> 01:12:42.984
Look out.
Ommadon's coming!

01:12:43.276 --> 01:12:45.027
You think he can help you?

01:13:04.171 --> 01:13:06.631
S-s-smrgol?

01:13:06.841 --> 01:13:07.925
Yes?

01:13:08.801 --> 01:13:13.301
[Weakly 1 ah, that's a --
a backside maneuver.

01:13:13.764 --> 01:13:17.225
I, uh -- well, that was one

01:13:17.435 --> 01:13:21.935
i-i failed...To mention.

01:13:22.857 --> 01:13:25.192
Easy.
Easy, old friend.

01:13:27.111 --> 01:13:28.237
I think --.

01:13:29.196 --> 01:13:32.949
I think something's
burst inside of me.

01:13:33.242 --> 01:13:37.162
L-i think my heart's gone.

01:13:38.956 --> 01:13:43.335
But -- but i-l did
do him in, huh?

01:13:43.836 --> 01:13:46.588
Yes.
Yes, you certainly did.

01:13:50.968 --> 01:13:53.929
What a grand -- grand way

01:13:54.138 --> 01:13:58.638
to finish a glorious...Life.

01:14:10.071 --> 01:14:12.907
<i>Melisande: And so they moved
through gormly gate.</i>

01:14:13.157 --> 01:14:16.618
<i>Arak: Oh, smrgol, how i
shall miss you, friend.</i>

01:14:17.078 --> 01:14:19.455
<i>And, lo, they enter...</i>

01:14:20.289 --> 01:14:22.958
<i>The realm of the red death.</i>

01:14:27.630 --> 01:14:29.923
Easy, lancer.
Easy, boy.

01:14:30.257 --> 01:14:32.884
Just a stagnant stream.
We can Ford it.

01:14:33.386 --> 01:14:35.429
Wait. I know that smell.

01:14:37.264 --> 01:14:38.181
Don't go near it!

01:14:38.432 --> 01:14:39.975
Danielle,
take one of your arrows

01:14:40.184 --> 01:14:41.351
and shoot it
into the stream.

01:14:41.560 --> 01:14:43.937
Waste an arrow?
We'll need all we have.

01:14:44.480 --> 01:14:46.815
I'd do as he says.

01:14:51.988 --> 01:14:54.949
By my father!
What is that slime?

01:14:55.199 --> 01:14:58.285
Dark magic, that's what --
dark magic.

01:14:58.494 --> 01:15:01.330
Maybe. But it's also
a highly corrosive acid

01:15:01.539 --> 01:15:03.958
much stronger than anything
i ever ran into at the lab.

01:15:04.542 --> 01:15:06.669
It's got a sulfur base, though.
That's what I smelled.

01:15:07.003 --> 01:15:08.879
You <i>do</i> speak in riddles,
old man.

01:15:09.255 --> 01:15:11.257
[Sniffing 1

01:15:11.465 --> 01:15:14.468
what's causing
the horrible muck?

01:15:18.055 --> 01:15:19.431
What is it?

01:15:26.147 --> 01:15:28.607
Arak: The worm of sligoth.

01:15:30.776 --> 01:15:34.154
[ Roaring 1

01:15:37.783 --> 01:15:39.242
I never saw one
that big.

01:15:39.452 --> 01:15:41.495
If lancer can get me
in and out quickly enough,

01:15:41.871 --> 01:15:43.956
I believe I can behead
the scummy thing.

01:15:44.206 --> 01:15:45.498
It wouldn't do any good.

01:15:45.708 --> 01:15:47.292
Chop it up
in a hundred parts,

01:15:47.501 --> 01:15:50.629
and each one would live
to spread the slime.

01:15:50.838 --> 01:15:51.964
Do we make a run for it?

01:15:52.214 --> 01:15:53.173
Too chancy.

01:15:55.968 --> 01:15:58.595
Oh, the worm is filthy.

01:15:58.804 --> 01:16:00.013
Steady, lass.

01:16:00.347 --> 01:16:02.474
Peter,
drive the others away.

01:16:02.975 --> 01:16:04.518
I'll remain
and do what I can.

01:16:05.478 --> 01:16:07.271
I'll not take flight.

01:16:07.730 --> 01:16:10.107
Either I'll have worm
for supper tonight,

01:16:10.316 --> 01:16:12.401
or worm sups on bone.

01:16:12.818 --> 01:16:14.069
No, there's a better way.

01:16:40.638 --> 01:16:42.056
Sir orren:
Peter, are you intact?

01:16:43.808 --> 01:16:46.977
Used up all my fire, though.
No lift left.

01:16:47.186 --> 01:16:48.770
Don't know
if anyone's thought of this,

01:16:48.979 --> 01:16:50.355
but after that display,

01:16:50.564 --> 01:16:52.649
ommadon's sure to know
we're here.

01:16:56.987 --> 01:16:59.823
These replicas
of our visitors

01:17:00.533 --> 01:17:04.537
are exact
to the smallest detail.

01:17:05.496 --> 01:17:09.996
Perhaps they can handle
ogres and worms...

01:17:13.629 --> 01:17:16.548
But see how they fare

01:17:16.882 --> 01:17:20.427
with the evil arts of ommadon.

01:17:35.359 --> 01:17:39.029
No! No!
Most terrible!

01:17:39.238 --> 01:17:41.531
What is it, daughter?
What does your mind see?

01:17:41.824 --> 01:17:45.536
A grasping hand,
dark and fearsome,

01:17:45.828 --> 01:17:48.330
to rob them of their will
and courage --

01:17:48.706 --> 01:17:51.625
<i>to take their hearts
and extinguish all hope.</i>

01:17:51.834 --> 01:17:55.629
<i>A spell -- an evil,
black-magic spell.</i>

01:17:59.008 --> 01:18:02.761
Press on, you say?
What's the use?

01:18:03.554 --> 01:18:05.806
The cause is hopeless.

01:18:06.348 --> 01:18:09.851
Aye. We've killed a worm.
What's that?

01:18:10.311 --> 01:18:11.895
Wait.
What are you talking about?

01:18:12.146 --> 01:18:16.150
I am just a little man,
but my foolishness is great.

01:18:16.734 --> 01:18:20.320
I belong in the trees,
the forest, not here.

01:18:20.654 --> 01:18:24.741
My arrows -- no matter how true,
what good are they here?

01:18:24.950 --> 01:18:27.202
I don't believe my ears!

01:18:27.453 --> 01:18:30.372
Well, fool...

01:18:30.998 --> 01:18:34.418
Tricked by carolinus
to bring us here.

01:18:34.793 --> 01:18:36.711
[Crying 1

01:18:44.887 --> 01:18:46.847
Peter:
They are bewitched, surely.

01:18:47.097 --> 01:18:49.099
<i>Solarius: Listen, Peter
of beacon street!</i>

01:18:49.308 --> 01:18:51.768
<i>Listen to me
before it gets to you!</i>

01:18:51.977 --> 01:18:55.605
Uh, what? Who --

01:18:55.981 --> 01:18:59.192
a blue wizard?
Solarius.

01:18:59.526 --> 01:19:02.403
<i>Was the shield of saturn
not given to you?</i>

01:19:02.613 --> 01:19:04.114
The shield?

01:19:04.949 --> 01:19:06.241
Oh, yes.
Carolinus said --

01:19:06.450 --> 01:19:09.286
<i>it will protect you
from ommadon's spells.</i>

01:19:09.495 --> 01:19:11.121
<i>Find the shield, son,</i>

01:19:11.413 --> 01:19:14.666
<i>and drive this
obscene force away.</i>

01:19:19.505 --> 01:19:21.256
Easy, boy. Easy.

01:19:28.138 --> 01:19:30.473
Away! Away!

01:19:39.108 --> 01:19:40.818
What's this?

01:19:41.402 --> 01:19:43.695
How dare he?

01:19:44.530 --> 01:19:47.032
How dare he?

01:19:48.409 --> 01:19:50.244
[Growling 1

01:19:50.452 --> 01:19:52.495
yes, briag...

01:19:53.247 --> 01:19:56.583
Lt's your turn now --

01:19:57.167 --> 01:20:00.170
you and your legions.

01:20:00.504 --> 01:20:01.588
Attack!

01:20:02.381 --> 01:20:04.341
Demolish!

01:20:04.717 --> 01:20:06.468
Devour!

01:20:07.219 --> 01:20:08.762
Burn!

01:20:08.971 --> 01:20:11.598
Grind them to dust!

01:20:12.182 --> 01:20:13.558
Go forth,

01:20:13.767 --> 01:20:18.267
and death be thy destination!

01:20:19.690 --> 01:20:22.275
Doom...Doom.

01:20:23.152 --> 01:20:24.945
[ Growls 1

01:20:25.487 --> 01:20:28.948
a flight of dragons --

01:20:29.992 --> 01:20:32.244
I command it!

01:20:39.543 --> 01:20:44.043
The flight...Of dragons!

01:20:45.299 --> 01:20:49.799
Doom...Doom...Doom...Doom.

01:20:54.975 --> 01:20:55.725
Look!

01:20:56.852 --> 01:20:58.103
Sir orren: Dragons!

01:20:59.938 --> 01:21:00.772
Dozens of them!

01:21:01.315 --> 01:21:02.149
Hopeless!

01:21:02.358 --> 01:21:06.445
It may be hopeless, but I'll
take a few before they get me.

01:21:06.653 --> 01:21:08.237
Let <i>me</i> take briag.

01:21:08.447 --> 01:21:11.658
If I die,
let me die a dragon killer!

01:21:12.743 --> 01:21:14.578
No offense, gorbash,

01:21:14.953 --> 01:21:18.122
but I suddenly hunger
for dragon!

01:21:18.540 --> 01:21:20.458
Wait.
We've got a chance.

01:21:20.751 --> 01:21:23.628
Sir orren, in your saddlepack --
the tiny golden flute --

01:21:23.837 --> 01:21:25.004
give it to giles.

01:21:26.965 --> 01:21:29.175
Now pipe us a tune.

01:21:34.598 --> 01:21:35.640
Quickly!

01:22:12.052 --> 01:22:15.263
And they are down --
all the dragons.

01:22:15.472 --> 01:22:16.931
Destroyed?

01:22:17.141 --> 01:22:18.100
Asleep.

01:22:18.434 --> 01:22:20.102
<i>But an enchanted sleep.</i>

01:22:20.686 --> 01:22:21.478
When they awaken,

01:22:21.687 --> 01:22:23.980
ommadon's spell over them
will be broken.

01:22:24.273 --> 01:22:25.649
They will join us!

01:22:26.066 --> 01:22:29.319
The red crown of ommadon
may soon be ours!

01:22:29.528 --> 01:22:34.028
Nay, father, nay.
One still is awake --

01:22:35.659 --> 01:22:36.743
briag.

01:22:37.202 --> 01:22:40.830
Ommadon's power over him
is stronger than lotagal's.

01:22:41.331 --> 01:22:44.459
He has blood on his mind
and can take them all.

01:22:44.751 --> 01:22:46.252
Peter will fight him.

01:22:46.587 --> 01:22:47.379
No, father.

01:22:48.213 --> 01:22:51.466
Peter, being a dragon,
now sleeps, too.

01:22:52.468 --> 01:22:55.137
Awaken, old boy!
We've won!

01:22:55.471 --> 01:22:57.431
I've never seen
such a sleep!

01:22:57.639 --> 01:22:59.974
Puny scum of carolinus,

01:23:00.642 --> 01:23:02.393
prepare to die!

01:23:19.495 --> 01:23:21.455
[ Roaring 1

01:23:29.171 --> 01:23:30.380
no!

01:23:33.717 --> 01:23:37.220
Oh, my darling...Dead.

01:23:37.554 --> 01:23:39.389
[Crying 1

01:23:46.188 --> 01:23:50.688
I'll crush you both,
you filthy crawly.

01:23:51.109 --> 01:23:52.443
Ahh!

01:23:52.653 --> 01:23:54.196
Ahh!

01:23:59.785 --> 01:24:03.789
Giles. My darling Danielle
and arak, too.

01:24:05.958 --> 01:24:08.460
Blade with whom I have lived,

01:24:08.752 --> 01:24:11.463
blade with whom I now die,

01:24:11.922 --> 01:24:15.467
serve right and justice
one last time.

01:24:15.884 --> 01:24:18.636
Seek one last heart of evil,

01:24:19.137 --> 01:24:21.889
still one last life of pain.

01:24:22.599 --> 01:24:24.267
Cut well, old friend --

01:24:25.060 --> 01:24:27.312
then...Farewell.

01:24:28.689 --> 01:24:29.648
Praying?

01:24:33.860 --> 01:24:35.778
Now die.

01:25:00.012 --> 01:25:03.557
I would have lived a life
with thee, Lassie,

01:25:04.808 --> 01:25:06.851
so now I die.

01:25:25.996 --> 01:25:30.496
I...Am...Victorious!

01:25:31.251 --> 01:25:33.336
Not quite yet.

01:25:38.467 --> 01:25:41.636
Well, well, well...

01:25:42.346 --> 01:25:44.139
The scientist.

01:25:45.557 --> 01:25:50.057
And how did you shed dragon,
filthy little man-thing?

01:25:50.937 --> 01:25:54.649
As gorbash slept, I suddenly
felt myself, Peter Dickinson,

01:25:54.858 --> 01:25:58.486
and I thought, "two things
cannot occupy the same place

01:25:58.695 --> 01:25:59.862
at the same time,"

01:26:00.113 --> 01:26:01.781
and the moment
i comprehended that,

01:26:02.407 --> 01:26:03.199
<i>volla.</i>

01:26:03.617 --> 01:26:05.619
I guess logic <i>is</i> stronger
than magic.

01:26:05.827 --> 01:26:09.121
Stronger than my magic?

01:26:14.044 --> 01:26:15.920
Noooooooo!

01:26:17.506 --> 01:26:22.006
L...Have gathered...
The sum total

01:26:23.762 --> 01:26:25.513
of the world's evil

01:26:25.722 --> 01:26:28.599
in one place,

01:26:28.809 --> 01:26:32.062
and that place is me!

01:26:36.900 --> 01:26:41.400
I...Am...Invincible!

01:26:42.739 --> 01:26:46.200
No magic stronger!

01:26:48.120 --> 01:26:51.081
L...Am the world,

01:26:52.082 --> 01:26:56.002
and the world is ommadon.

01:27:06.972 --> 01:27:10.684
I can do anything!
Test me!

01:27:11.184 --> 01:27:14.020
Allow me to reach up
and pluck down the sun.

01:27:14.521 --> 01:27:15.563
You can't do that.

01:27:15.772 --> 01:27:20.272
Why?! Why, you insect?!
Why?!

01:27:20.736 --> 01:27:23.363
Seven heads,
and each one a simpleton.

01:27:23.655 --> 01:27:25.239
Don't you know
what you reach for

01:27:25.449 --> 01:27:27.325
isn't in that position
anymore?

01:27:27.534 --> 01:27:30.203
The sun is the sun!

01:27:30.620 --> 01:27:32.038
I can see where it is!

01:27:32.247 --> 01:27:33.873
Where it was, pipsqueak.

01:27:34.082 --> 01:27:35.249
Any schoolboy knows

01:27:35.459 --> 01:27:39.959
that light travels
at 186,300 miles per second.

01:27:40.255 --> 01:27:43.549
What you see is the sun's
position 8 1/2 minutes ago.

01:27:43.925 --> 01:27:47.136
No magic but mine
can move the sun!

01:27:47.679 --> 01:27:49.138
I command it!

01:27:49.347 --> 01:27:52.308
Not magic, gashead --
mathematics.

01:27:52.684 --> 01:27:55.353
And that's the answer
to why antiquity chose me.

01:27:55.562 --> 01:27:57.146
You are magic <i>--</i>
mere illusion.

01:27:57.355 --> 01:28:01.692
I am science <i>--</i>
logic and the truth.

01:28:02.235 --> 01:28:04.445
[ Roaring 1

01:28:06.948 --> 01:28:08.074
you don't frighten me.

01:28:08.283 --> 01:28:10.285
Nothing so horrible
could be real.

01:28:10.786 --> 01:28:12.078
I deny you!

01:28:12.454 --> 01:28:16.374
Deny me,
and you deny all magic.

01:28:17.793 --> 01:28:19.294
Say it, then!

01:28:19.503 --> 01:28:22.422
I deny all magic!

01:28:24.007 --> 01:28:26.592
Deny this...

01:28:38.855 --> 01:28:40.606
Those incantations
can't hurt me.

01:28:40.816 --> 01:28:43.026
I have some incantations
of my own.

01:28:43.360 --> 01:28:47.197
How about "a body in motion
tends to stay in motion"?

01:28:47.489 --> 01:28:51.989
"Protons have 1,832 times
the mass of electrons."

01:28:55.580 --> 01:28:57.164
"All light is bent
or refracted

01:28:57.374 --> 01:28:59.376
"as it goes from one medium
to another,

01:28:59.584 --> 01:29:01.794
"save in a direction
perpendicular to the interface

01:29:02.003 --> 01:29:03.504
between the two mediums..."

01:29:03.713 --> 01:29:08.213
Aaaaaaaah!

01:29:09.469 --> 01:29:11.596
"...upon the variations
from their specific type

01:29:11.805 --> 01:29:13.681
which individuals present."

01:29:14.349 --> 01:29:16.934
"Gravity varies as to the
inverse square of the distance."

01:29:17.143 --> 01:29:19.603
"The velocity of light
is equal to the wavelength

01:29:19.813 --> 01:29:21.856
times the frequency
of vibration..."

01:29:22.983 --> 01:29:25.193
Aaaaaah!

01:29:25.402 --> 01:29:28.613
"...are determined by the masses
present in space and time."

01:29:28.822 --> 01:29:32.867
Aaaaaaaaaaah!

01:29:33.410 --> 01:29:37.910
Come, devils, witches,
demons, ogres, trolls,

01:29:38.540 --> 01:29:41.834
sandmurks, harpies,
ghouls, sorcerers.

01:29:42.294 --> 01:29:45.338
Come algebra, anatomy,
astronomy, biology,

01:29:45.547 --> 01:29:48.383
chemistry, geology,
geometry, mathematics,

01:29:48.592 --> 01:29:51.011
meteorology, mineralogy,
oceanography,

01:29:51.219 --> 01:29:54.513
paleontology, physics,
psychology, sociology,

01:29:54.723 --> 01:29:56.599
trigonometry, and zoology.

01:29:56.808 --> 01:30:00.770
Aaaaaaaaaaah!

01:30:27.589 --> 01:30:31.467
Behold, my darling --
the magic realm!

01:30:31.676 --> 01:30:32.843
And look!

01:30:40.685 --> 01:30:43.312
Caroli-i-i-nus!

01:30:57.327 --> 01:30:58.453
I am home.

01:31:00.747 --> 01:31:02.749
<i>We</i> are home.

01:31:02.958 --> 01:31:07.458
Well, gorbash,
awake at last?

01:31:08.755 --> 01:31:12.425
Arak! I thought you were dead
beneath the sea!

01:31:13.385 --> 01:31:15.428
No.

01:31:16.096 --> 01:31:16.930
Old friend!

01:31:17.222 --> 01:31:19.557
Oh, thank heaven,
you're still intact!

01:31:19.766 --> 01:31:22.393
We've won!
Sir Peter, we've won!

01:31:22.727 --> 01:31:23.853
I don't understand.

01:31:24.062 --> 01:31:27.732
Why the blazes do you call me
by this man name?

01:31:27.941 --> 01:31:29.275
Gorbash?

01:31:29.526 --> 01:31:31.152
Of course gorbash.

01:31:31.361 --> 01:31:33.029
Why so shocked,
sir orren --

01:31:33.363 --> 01:31:35.656
you who practically
hatched me?

01:31:35.865 --> 01:31:37.992
Sir Peter is gone.

01:31:38.201 --> 01:31:40.036
Gone?! Where?!

01:31:40.495 --> 01:31:41.829
As carolinus hoped,

01:31:42.038 --> 01:31:45.833
he used his knowledge
of science to deny magic.

01:31:46.167 --> 01:31:49.420
By denying magic,
he is lost to us forever.

01:31:49.629 --> 01:31:50.504
Melisande: Father!

01:31:50.714 --> 01:31:53.133
Melisande!
She's awake!

01:31:53.591 --> 01:31:56.343
Father!
Sir Peter was here!

01:31:56.553 --> 01:31:58.721
Yes. Yes, my darling.

01:31:59.014 --> 01:31:59.848
Look!

01:32:00.306 --> 01:32:02.182
The crown of ommadon.

01:32:02.767 --> 01:32:05.478
As foretold,
it awakened you.

01:32:05.687 --> 01:32:08.690
No. The kiss awakened me.

01:32:09.024 --> 01:32:10.150
The kiss?

01:32:11.067 --> 01:32:12.902
<i>I was lost
in that sleep of death.</i>

01:32:13.528 --> 01:32:15.696
<i>Then I felt his lips
upon mine.</i>

01:32:16.072 --> 01:32:17.698
<i>I opened my eyes,</i>

01:32:17.907 --> 01:32:20.075
<i>and, for an instant,
i saw his smile.</i>

01:32:21.161 --> 01:32:22.370
<i>Then he was gone.</i>

01:32:23.788 --> 01:32:25.539
<i>Awakened you
with a kiss, eh?</i>

01:32:26.541 --> 01:32:31.041
<i>Well, perhaps he isn't
completely lost to magic.</i>

01:32:32.297 --> 01:32:36.050
May -- may I join him,
father?

01:32:36.593 --> 01:32:38.386
Of all questions,

01:32:39.095 --> 01:32:40.721
I feared that the most.

01:32:41.890 --> 01:32:42.765
May I?

01:32:43.433 --> 01:32:45.601
That must be
your decision, child.

01:32:46.728 --> 01:32:51.065
Go...And you may never return
to the magic realm,

01:32:51.483 --> 01:32:53.818
for even now, the great dome
of lnvisibility

01:32:54.027 --> 01:32:55.069
grows over our world

01:32:55.278 --> 01:32:57.780
to protect its sanctity
for all time,

01:32:58.656 --> 01:33:01.450
and no one on the outside
may enter its boundaries,

01:33:01.910 --> 01:33:06.080
save for the length of a dream
or flash of an inspiration.

01:33:06.998 --> 01:33:09.667
But it will stay
through the years

01:33:09.876 --> 01:33:11.627
and the centuries
and the ages

01:33:11.920 --> 01:33:14.297
a part of man for all time,

01:33:14.964 --> 01:33:19.464
and whenever man needs magic,
we will be here.

01:33:23.765 --> 01:33:24.974
11!

01:33:25.183 --> 01:33:27.977
Your dragon fire
melts my ice!

01:33:28.186 --> 01:33:30.229
Oh! You win!

01:33:30.647 --> 01:33:32.607
Look, I gotta get back
to work.

01:33:33.066 --> 01:33:35.943
Wait a minute.
I do have some business now.

01:33:36.152 --> 01:33:38.279
I told you
that watch of yours --

01:33:38.655 --> 01:33:39.822
not the watch.

01:33:40.448 --> 01:33:41.115
This.

01:33:41.324 --> 01:33:42.908
Ye gods!

01:33:43.243 --> 01:33:44.494
Solid gold!

01:33:45.161 --> 01:33:46.328
Where did you find this?

01:33:46.663 --> 01:33:49.082
Oh, I had a horde.

01:33:49.290 --> 01:33:51.417
I don't blame you
for not telling.

01:33:51.626 --> 01:33:53.336
You can live off this
for years!

01:33:53.628 --> 01:33:57.089
Travel --
Europe, Asia, cruises.

01:33:57.423 --> 01:34:00.300
No. I'll be satisfied
with a cottage

01:34:00.677 --> 01:34:03.221
surrounded by trees
near a stream...

01:34:04.472 --> 01:34:05.723
Like one I used to know.

01:34:07.267 --> 01:34:09.727
Oh. Can I help you, miss?

01:34:11.855 --> 01:34:15.024
Where do you kids
get these things?

01:34:16.776 --> 01:34:18.152
Melisande!
